WEBVTT

01:10.320 --> 01:11.652
<i>Longing</i>

01:13.824 --> 01:14.824
<i>Rusted</i>

01:15.367 --> 01:16.367
<i>Se venteen</i>

01:16.994 --> 01:17.994
<i>Daybreak</i>

01:19.079 --> 01:20.195
<i>Furnace</i>

01:21.540 --> 01:22.540
<i>Nine</i>

01:23.041 --> 01:24.498
<i>Benign</i>

01:25.586 --> 01:27.327
<i>Homecoming</i>

01:28.338 --> 01:29.374
<i>One</i>

01:31.300 --> 01:33.383
<i>Freight car</i>

01:41.018 --> 01:42.018
Good morning, Soldier.

01:44.730 --> 01:45.811
Ready to comply.

01:47.357 --> 01:48.564
I have a mission for you.

01:50.527 --> 01:52.063
Sanction and extract.

01:52.904 --> 01:54.270
No witnesses.

02:36.073 --> 02:37.655
Well done Soldier.

03:21.410 --> 03:23.618
<i>All right, what do you see?</i>

03:23.787 --> 03:25.779
Standard beat cops.

03:26.915 --> 03:28.497
Small station.

03:30.669 --> 03:31.785
Quiet street.

03:32.295 --> 03:33.786
<i>It's a good target.</i>

03:33.964 --> 03:36.081
There's an ATM on the
south corner, which means?

03:36.258 --> 03:37.294
Cameras.

03:37.467 --> 03:39.129
<i>Both cross streets are one-way.</i>

03:39.302 --> 03:40.838
So, compromised escape routes.

03:41.638 --> 03:43.425
Means our guy doesn't
care about being seen.

03:43.515 --> 03:45.598
He isn't afraid
to make a mess on the way out.

03:45.934 --> 03:47.734
You see that Range Rover
halfway up the block?

03:47.853 --> 03:49.719
Yeah, the red one? It's cute.

03:49.813 --> 03:50.929
<i>It's also bulletproof,</i>

03:51.022 --> 03:52.263
<i>which means private security...</i>

03:52.357 --> 03:53.768
<i>which means more guns...</i>

03:54.109 --> 03:56.442
<i>which means more headaches
for somebody. Probably us.</i>

03:56.528 --> 03:59.020
You guys know
I can move things with my mind, right?

03:59.406 --> 04:01.898
Looking over your shoulder
needs to become second nature.

04:02.451 --> 04:04.818
Anybody ever tell you
you're a little paranoid?

04:04.911 --> 04:07.198
<i>Not to my face.
Why? Did you hear something?</i>

04:07.330 --> 04:08.491
<i>Eyes on target, folks.</i>

04:08.707 --> 04:10.307
This is the best lead
we've had on Rumlow

04:10.333 --> 04:11.769
in six months. I don't want to lose him.

04:11.793 --> 04:14.080
If he sees us coming,
that won't be a problem.

04:14.171 --> 04:15.503
He kind of hates us.

04:19.176 --> 04:20.257
Sam...

04:20.427 --> 04:21.838
see that garbage truck?

04:22.012 --> 04:23.219
Tag it.

04:41.782 --> 04:42.863
Give me X-ray.

04:48.038 --> 04:49.700
That truck's loaded for max weight.

04:49.915 --> 04:50.915
And the driver's armed.

04:51.041 --> 04:52.041
It's a battering ram.

04:52.209 --> 04:53.209
<i>- Go now.</i>
- What?

04:54.419 --> 04:55.580
He's not hitting the police.

05:59.818 --> 06:01.730
Body armour, AR-15s.

06:01.945 --> 06:03.481
<i>I make seven hostiles.</i>

06:12.289 --> 06:13.655
I make five.

06:18.378 --> 06:20.165
Sam.

06:23.717 --> 06:24.798
Four.

06:29.306 --> 06:30.717
Rumlow's on the third floor.

06:30.807 --> 06:32.173
Wanda, just like we practised.

06:32.350 --> 06:33.350
What about the gas?

06:33.476 --> 06:34.512
Get it out.

06:52.495 --> 06:53.531
Pack it up.

07:31.034 --> 07:32.115
He's here.

07:35.956 --> 07:37.367
Rumlow has a biological weapon.

07:37.540 --> 07:38.872
<i>I'm on it.</i>

08:14.077 --> 08:15.909
I don't work like that no more.

08:19.082 --> 08:20.082
Fire in the hole.

08:25.588 --> 08:26.624
No!

08:49.571 --> 08:50.607
Sam.

08:50.822 --> 08:52.939
<i>He's in an AFV heading north.</i>

08:57.620 --> 08:59.612
Take this to the airstrip.

08:59.789 --> 09:01.781
We're not gonna outrun them.
Lose the truck.

09:09.215 --> 09:10.443
Where are you going to meet us?

09:10.467 --> 09:11.958
I'm not.

09:23.229 --> 09:25.016
I've got four, they're splitting up.

09:29.903 --> 09:31.485
I got the two on the left.

09:39.996 --> 09:41.203
They ditched their gear.

09:41.372 --> 09:43.372
It's a shell game now.
One of them has the payload.

09:49.255 --> 09:51.087
There you are, you son of a bitch.

09:52.133 --> 09:53.419
I've been waiting for this.

10:10.860 --> 10:12.021
He doesn't have it.

10:12.487 --> 10:13.487
I'm empty!

10:13.696 --> 10:14.937
Out of the way!

10:54.404 --> 10:55.565
Drop it.

10:55.947 --> 10:56.947
Or I'll drop this.

10:58.741 --> 11:00.528
- Drop it!
- He'll do it!

11:07.834 --> 11:09.746
Payload secure. Thanks, Sam.

11:09.961 --> 11:10.961
Don't thank me.

11:11.087 --> 11:12.669
I'm not thanking that thing.

11:12.922 --> 11:13.922
His name is Redwing.

11:14.090 --> 11:15.251
<i>I'm still not thanking it.</i>

11:15.341 --> 11:16.501
He's cute. Go ahead, pet him.

11:23.266 --> 11:24.266
Come on!

11:32.483 --> 11:34.566
This is for dropping
a building on my face.

11:52.837 --> 11:53.873
Ahh!

11:56.841 --> 11:58.777
I think I look pretty good,
all things considered.

11:58.801 --> 11:59.801
Who's your buyer?

12:00.178 --> 12:01.965
You know, he knew you.

12:02.138 --> 12:04.175
Your pal, your buddy, your Bucky.

12:05.808 --> 12:06.808
What did you say?

12:06.935 --> 12:08.642
He remembered you.

12:09.145 --> 12:11.683
I was there. He got all weepy about it.

12:13.191 --> 12:14.978
Till they put his brain back in a blender.

12:15.902 --> 12:17.643
He wanted you to know something.

12:17.737 --> 12:18.773
He said to me...

12:19.322 --> 12:21.359
"Please tell Rogers.

12:21.991 --> 12:23.232
"When you gotta go...

12:23.451 --> 12:25.158
"you gotta go."

12:27.497 --> 12:28.613
And you're coming with me.

12:45.598 --> 12:47.260
Oh, my...

12:50.019 --> 12:51.351
Sam...

12:53.189 --> 12:54.475
we need Fire and Rescue

12:54.565 --> 12:56.181
on the south side of the building.

12:56.734 --> 12:58.270
We gotta get up there.

13:05.159 --> 13:11.781
<i>Try to remember the kind of September</i>

13:11.874 --> 13:15.618
<i>When grass was green</i>

13:16.629 --> 13:19.042
Wake up, dear,
and say goodbye to your father.

13:19.215 --> 13:20.831
Who's the homeless person
on the couch?

13:22.302 --> 13:24.385
This is why
I love coming home for Christmas...

13:24.554 --> 13:25.795
right before you leave town.

13:25.972 --> 13:28.214
Be nice, dear,
he's been studying abroad.

13:28.391 --> 13:30.223
Really? Which broad?
What's her name?

13:30.393 --> 13:31.725
Candice.

13:32.228 --> 13:33.309
Do me a favour?

13:33.396 --> 13:35.040
Try not to burn
the house down before Monday.

13:35.064 --> 13:36.225
Okay, so it's Monday.

13:36.399 --> 13:37.560
That is good to know,

13:37.650 --> 13:39.562
I will plan my toga party accordingly.

13:40.320 --> 13:41.401
Where you going?

13:41.571 --> 13:42.652
Your father's flying us

13:42.739 --> 13:44.179
to the Bahamas for a little getaway.

13:44.240 --> 13:45.731
We might have to make a quick stop.

13:45.825 --> 13:47.987
At the Pentagon. Right?

13:48.077 --> 13:51.161
Don't worry, you're gonna love
the holiday menu at the commissary.

13:51.247 --> 13:53.990
They say sarcasm
is a metric for potential.

13:54.083 --> 13:55.995
If that's true,
you'll be a great man someday.

13:56.169 --> 13:57.501
I'll get the bags.

13:59.964 --> 14:02.331
He does miss you when you're not here.

14:04.093 --> 14:07.427
And frankly, you're going to miss us.

14:08.139 --> 14:09.846
Because this is the last time

14:09.932 --> 14:11.514
we're all going to be together.

14:12.435 --> 14:14.802
You know what's about to happen.

14:15.355 --> 14:16.766
Say something.

14:16.856 --> 14:18.939
If you don't, you'll regret it.

14:22.612 --> 14:24.103
I love you, Dad.

14:25.281 --> 14:27.523
And I know you did the best you could.

14:43.383 --> 14:45.340
That's how I wish it happened.

14:47.804 --> 14:50.387
Binarily Augmented Retro-Framing...

14:50.473 --> 14:51.589
or BARF.

14:51.682 --> 14:53.469
God, I gotta work on that acronym.

14:53.559 --> 14:55.926
An extremely costly method

14:56.020 --> 14:58.262
of hijacking the hippocampus...

14:58.356 --> 15:02.475
to clear traumatic memories.

15:05.154 --> 15:06.235
Huh.

15:06.364 --> 15:07.571
It doesn't change the fact

15:07.657 --> 15:09.489
that they never made it to the airport...

15:10.159 --> 15:13.197
or all the things I did to avoid
processing my grief, but...

15:15.164 --> 15:19.499
Plus, $611 million for my
little therapeutic experiment?

15:21.504 --> 15:24.212
No one in their right mind
would've ever funded it.

15:25.508 --> 15:28.046
Help me out,
what's the MIT mission statement?

15:28.219 --> 15:29.460
"To generate, disseminate...

15:30.847 --> 15:32.338
"and preserve knowledge.

15:32.932 --> 15:34.594
"And work with others...

15:34.684 --> 15:37.518
"to bring it to bear on
the world's great challenges."

15:38.521 --> 15:41.264
Well, you are the others.

15:42.525 --> 15:43.857
And, quiet as it's kept...

15:43.943 --> 15:45.605
the challenges facing you

15:45.695 --> 15:47.215
are the greatest mankind's ever known.

15:47.530 --> 15:49.897
Plus, most of you are broke.

15:50.032 --> 15:51.944
Oh, I'm sorry. Rather, you were.

15:52.118 --> 15:53.359
As of this moment...

15:53.536 --> 15:55.778
every student has been made
an equal recipient...

15:55.872 --> 15:58.865
of the inaugural
September Foundation Grant.

15:58.958 --> 16:00.449
As in...

16:00.877 --> 16:03.460
all of your projects have
just been approved and funded.

16:06.716 --> 16:09.299
No strings, no taxes...

16:09.469 --> 16:11.631
just reframe the future!

16:11.804 --> 16:13.466
Starting now.

16:23.316 --> 16:24.316
Go break some eggs.

16:32.074 --> 16:33.781
Wow. Wow.

16:35.411 --> 16:37.573
That took my breath away.

16:37.747 --> 16:39.158
Oh, Tony! So generous.

16:39.332 --> 16:41.494
So much money! Wow!

16:41.667 --> 16:43.408
Out of curiosity...

16:43.586 --> 16:46.374
will any portion of that grant
be made available to faculty?

16:46.464 --> 16:47.900
I know, "Ooh, gross," but hear me out.

16:47.924 --> 16:50.166
I have got this killer idea
for a self-cooking hotdog.

16:50.259 --> 16:51.403
Basically,
chemical detonator embedded...

16:51.427 --> 16:52.446
Restroom's this way, yeah?

16:52.470 --> 16:53.655
Yeah. Embedded in the meat shaft.

16:53.679 --> 16:56.012
Mr Stark, I am so sorry
about the teleprompter.

16:56.098 --> 16:57.576
I didn't know Miss Potts had cancelled.

16:57.600 --> 16:59.341
They didn't have time to fix it.

17:00.978 --> 17:02.935
It's fine. I'll be right back.

17:03.272 --> 17:04.433
We'll catch up later.

17:22.625 --> 17:25.459
That was nice,
what you did for those young people.

17:26.128 --> 17:27.619
Ah, they deserve it.

17:27.797 --> 17:29.959
Plus, it helps ease my conscience.

17:30.550 --> 17:35.136
They say there's a correlation
between generosity and guilt.

17:36.222 --> 17:38.805
But if you've got the money...

17:39.684 --> 17:41.801
break as many eggs as you like.

17:42.562 --> 17:43.928
Right?

17:52.697 --> 17:53.697
Are you going up?

17:54.156 --> 17:56.193
I'm right where I want to be.

17:56.867 --> 17:58.074
Okay. Hey.

18:01.330 --> 18:04.038
Sorry, it's an occupational hazard.

18:04.333 --> 18:05.869
I work for the State Department.

18:06.669 --> 18:08.331
Human Resources.

18:08.838 --> 18:10.579
I know it's boring...

18:10.923 --> 18:14.166
but it enabled me to raise a son.

18:15.011 --> 18:17.924
I'm very proud of what he grew up to be.

18:19.932 --> 18:22.515
His name was Charlie Spencer.

18:24.895 --> 18:26.011
You murdered him.

18:27.690 --> 18:29.272
In Sokovia.

18:31.027 --> 18:34.111
Not that that matters in the least to you.

18:35.781 --> 18:37.898
You think you fight for us?

18:39.118 --> 18:41.360
You just fight for yourself.

18:42.788 --> 18:46.031
Who's going to avenge my son, Stark?

18:47.627 --> 18:49.209
He's dead...

18:49.462 --> 18:51.545
and I blame you.

19:00.097 --> 19:01.304
<i>11 Wakandans were</i>

19:01.390 --> 19:03.507
<i>among those killed
during a confrontation...</i>

19:03.601 --> 19:05.809
<i>between the Avengers
and a group of mercenaries...</i>

19:05.895 --> 19:07.932
<i>in Lagos, Nigeria last month.</i>

19:08.064 --> 19:09.541
<i>The traditionally reclusive Wakandans</i>

19:09.565 --> 19:10.851
<i>were on an outreach mission...</i>

19:10.941 --> 19:12.682
<i>in Lagos, when the attack occurred.</i>

19:12.902 --> 19:16.066
<i>Our people's blood is spilled
on foreign soil...</i>

19:16.906 --> 19:19.899
<i>not only because of
the actions of criminals...</i>

19:20.076 --> 19:23.911
<i>but by the indifference
of those pledged to stop them.</i>

19:23.996 --> 19:26.955
<i>Victory at the expense of the innocent...</i>

19:27.249 --> 19:29.411
<i>is no victory at all.</i>

19:29.627 --> 19:31.163
<i>The Wakandan king went on to...</i>

19:31.420 --> 19:32.877
<i>They are operating outside</i>

19:32.963 --> 19:34.704
<i>and above the international law.</i>

19:34.799 --> 19:36.006
<i>Because that's the reality,</i>

19:36.092 --> 19:37.674
<i>if we don't respond to acts like these.</i>

19:37.843 --> 19:39.835
<i>What legal authority does an enhanced</i>

19:39.929 --> 19:41.670
<i>individual like Wanda Maximoff have...</i>

19:41.764 --> 19:43.096
<i>to operate in Nigeri...?</i>

19:47.687 --> 19:48.928
It's my fault.

19:49.355 --> 19:50.355
That's not true.

19:50.523 --> 19:51.523
Turn the TV back on.

19:51.691 --> 19:53.728
They're being very specific.

19:54.110 --> 19:57.353
I should've clocked that bomb vest
long before you had to deal with it.

19:58.614 --> 20:00.150
Rumlow said "Bucky"...

20:01.659 --> 20:03.553
and all of a sudden
I was a 16-year-old kid again,

20:03.577 --> 20:04.613
in Brooklyn.

20:08.874 --> 20:10.456
And people died.

20:12.503 --> 20:13.503
It's on me.

20:14.296 --> 20:15.958
It's on both of us.

20:17.007 --> 20:18.373
This job...

20:21.303 --> 20:23.215
We try to save
as many people as we can.

20:24.223 --> 20:25.885
Sometimes that doesn't
mean everybody.

20:26.016 --> 20:27.973
But if we can't find a way
to live with that...

20:28.144 --> 20:30.056
then next time...

20:31.355 --> 20:33.142
maybe nobody gets saved.

20:37.403 --> 20:39.395
Vis! We talked about this.

20:39.488 --> 20:42.196
Yes, but the door was open
so I assumed that...

20:43.951 --> 20:46.910
Captain Rogers wished to know
when Mr Stark was arriving.

20:47.079 --> 20:48.536
Thank you. We'll be right down.

20:49.081 --> 20:51.243
I'll use the door.

20:52.251 --> 20:54.584
Oh, and apparently,
he's brought a guest.

20:54.754 --> 20:56.461
We know who it is?

20:56.630 --> 20:58.462
The Secretary of State.

21:01.594 --> 21:03.176
<i>Five years ago...</i>

21:03.679 --> 21:05.420
I had a heart attack...

21:05.723 --> 21:08.761
and dropped right in
the middle of my backswing.

21:09.560 --> 21:11.973
Turned out it was the best
round of my life...

21:12.146 --> 21:14.263
because after 13 hours of surgery

21:14.356 --> 21:16.143
and a triple bypass...

21:17.067 --> 21:20.811
I found something 40 years
in the Army had never taught me.

21:21.530 --> 21:22.691
Perspective.

21:24.909 --> 21:28.778
The world owes the Avengers
an unpayable debt.

21:29.622 --> 21:32.535
You have fought for us...

21:32.792 --> 21:35.830
protected us, risked your lives...

21:36.420 --> 21:40.130
but while a great many people
see you as heroes...

21:40.216 --> 21:42.208
there are some...

21:43.594 --> 21:45.551
who would prefer the word "vigilantes."

21:45.679 --> 21:47.966
What word would you use,
Mr Secretary?

21:48.140 --> 21:49.347
How about "dangerous"?

21:50.100 --> 21:52.808
What would you call
a group of US-based,

21:52.895 --> 21:55.012
enhanced individuals...

21:55.189 --> 21:58.148
who routinely ignore
sovereign borders...

21:58.317 --> 22:01.936
and inflict their will
wherever they choose...

22:02.112 --> 22:04.229
and who, frankly, seem unconcerned

22:04.323 --> 22:05.564
about what they leave behind?

22:10.579 --> 22:12.161
New York.

22:25.970 --> 22:27.711
Washington, D.C.

22:35.896 --> 22:37.307
Sokovia.

22:48.200 --> 22:49.200
Lagos.

22:58.544 --> 23:00.160
Okay. That's enough.

23:02.381 --> 23:03.462
For the past four years,

23:03.549 --> 23:05.026
you've operated with unlimited power...

23:05.050 --> 23:06.791
and no supervision.

23:07.052 --> 23:08.905
That's an arrangement
the governments of the world

23:08.929 --> 23:10.921
can no longer tolerate.

23:13.392 --> 23:15.805
But I think we have a solution.

23:19.565 --> 23:21.898
The Sokovia Accords.

23:22.568 --> 23:25.185
Approved by 117 countries...

23:25.362 --> 23:28.230
it states that the Avengers

23:28.324 --> 23:30.782
shall no longer be a private organisation.

23:30.993 --> 23:32.200
Instead...

23:32.453 --> 23:34.570
they'll operate under the supervision

23:34.663 --> 23:36.575
of a United Nations panel...

23:36.749 --> 23:41.084
only when and if that panel
deems it necessary.

23:42.379 --> 23:45.247
The Avengers were formed to
make the world a safer place.

23:45.758 --> 23:46.965
I feel we've done that.

23:47.343 --> 23:51.132
Tell me, Captain, do you know
where Thor and Banner are right now?

23:52.806 --> 23:54.923
If I misplaced a couple of
30 megaton nukes...

23:55.225 --> 23:57.433
you can bet there'd be consequences.

23:57.937 --> 24:02.147
Compromise. Reassurance.
That's how the world works.

24:02.399 --> 24:05.358
Believe me, this is the middle ground.

24:06.320 --> 24:08.903
So, there are contingencies.

24:09.365 --> 24:12.028
Three days from now,
the UN meets in Vienna...

24:12.201 --> 24:14.193
to ratify the Accords.

24:16.372 --> 24:17.954
Talk it over.

24:21.126 --> 24:23.288
And if we come
to a decision you don't like?

24:25.255 --> 24:26.837
Then you retire.

24:50.072 --> 24:51.072
Hello?

24:52.950 --> 24:55.033
Is this your car out front?

24:56.620 --> 24:58.407
I jumped the kerb.

25:00.040 --> 25:01.040
Maybe we could...

25:01.625 --> 25:03.161
take care of it ourselves.

25:03.335 --> 25:05.372
If you wanna call the cops,
that's okay, too...

25:05.546 --> 25:06.957
- I guess.
- No.

25:08.632 --> 25:10.419
No cops.

25:10.676 --> 25:11.676
Thank you.

25:49.798 --> 25:51.414
You have kept your looks, Colonel.

25:52.051 --> 25:53.051
Congratulations.

25:57.139 --> 26:01.133
"Mission report. December 16, 1991."

26:01.310 --> 26:02.767
Who are you?

26:03.979 --> 26:05.811
My name is Zemo.

26:06.982 --> 26:09.190
I will repeat my question.

26:09.818 --> 26:14.688
Mission report, December 16, 1991.

26:14.865 --> 26:16.652
How did you find me?

26:16.825 --> 26:18.782
When S.H.I.E.L.D. fell...

26:18.952 --> 26:22.411
Black Widow released
HYDRA files to the public.

26:22.581 --> 26:25.244
Millions of pages. Much of it encrypted.

26:25.334 --> 26:27.041
Not easy to decipher.

26:30.380 --> 26:32.246
But, I have experience.

26:33.133 --> 26:34.749
And patience.

26:36.136 --> 26:38.173
A man can do anything if he has those.

26:39.306 --> 26:40.422
What do you want?

26:41.683 --> 26:43.549
Mission report.

26:43.727 --> 26:45.559
December 16.

26:45.729 --> 26:47.140
1991.

26:47.898 --> 26:51.312
Go... to... hell!

27:05.499 --> 27:07.832
HYDRA deserves its place
on the ash heap.

27:08.460 --> 27:10.918
So your death would not bother me.

27:11.547 --> 27:13.504
But I'd have to use this book...

27:13.966 --> 27:17.175
and other bloodier methods
to find what I need.

27:17.344 --> 27:19.552
I don't look forward to that.

27:21.140 --> 27:23.348
You'd only be dying for...

27:23.517 --> 27:24.883
your pride.

27:39.658 --> 27:42.196
Hail HYDRA.

27:53.547 --> 27:56.005
Secretary Ross has
a Congressional Medal of Honour...

27:56.091 --> 27:57.371
which is one more than you have.

27:57.509 --> 27:59.171
So let's say we agree to this thing.

27:59.261 --> 28:01.093
How long is it gonna be
before they LoJack us

28:01.180 --> 28:02.500
like a bunch of common criminals?

28:02.639 --> 28:04.676
117 countries want to sign this.

28:04.766 --> 28:07.509
117, Sam, and you're just like,
"No, that's cool. We got it."

28:07.603 --> 28:08.746
How long are you going
to play both sides?

28:08.770 --> 28:09.931
I have an equation.

28:10.105 --> 28:11.971
Oh, this will clear it up.

28:12.524 --> 28:14.106
In the eight years since Mr Stark

28:14.193 --> 28:15.650
announced himself as Iron Man...

28:15.736 --> 28:19.195
the number of known enhanced persons
has grown exponentially.

28:20.908 --> 28:22.194
During the same period...

28:22.367 --> 28:24.484
the number of potentially
world-ending events

28:24.578 --> 28:26.114
has risen at a commensurate rate.

28:26.330 --> 28:27.571
Are you saying it's our fault?

28:27.998 --> 28:30.456
I'm saying there may be a causality.

28:32.461 --> 28:35.204
Our very strength invites challenge.

28:35.297 --> 28:37.914
Challenge incites conflict.

28:38.091 --> 28:39.878
And conflict...

28:41.428 --> 28:43.670
breeds catastrophe.

28:43.805 --> 28:45.216
Oversight...

28:47.643 --> 28:50.556
Oversight is not an idea that
can be dismissed out of hand.

28:50.812 --> 28:51.812
Boom.

28:52.689 --> 28:53.896
Tony.

28:54.066 --> 28:56.683
You are being uncharacteristically
non-hyperverbal.

28:56.860 --> 28:58.213
It's because he's already
made up his mind.

28:58.237 --> 29:00.103
Boy, you know me so well.

29:01.114 --> 29:03.606
Actually, I'm nursing
an electromagnetic headache.

29:04.493 --> 29:07.281
That's what's going on, Cap.
It's just pain.

29:08.538 --> 29:09.949
It's discomfort.

29:10.040 --> 29:12.032
Who's putting coffee grounds
in the disposal?

29:12.876 --> 29:15.493
Am I running a bed and breakfast
for a biker gang?

29:21.760 --> 29:23.376
Oh, that's Charles Spencer, by the way.

29:23.470 --> 29:24.881
He's a great kid.

29:25.138 --> 29:28.427
Computer engineering degree,
3.6 GPA...

29:28.642 --> 29:31.180
had a floor-level gig
at Intel planned for the fall.

29:31.436 --> 29:33.769
But first, he wanted to put
a few miles on his soul...

29:34.147 --> 29:36.639
before he parked it
behind a desk. See the world.

29:36.858 --> 29:38.315
Maybe be of service.

29:39.069 --> 29:40.546
Charlie didn't want to go to Vegas or

29:40.570 --> 29:42.090
Fort Lauderdale,
which is what I would do.

29:42.114 --> 29:44.822
He didn't go to Paris or Amsterdam,
which sounds fun.

29:44.992 --> 29:46.949
He decided to spend his summer

29:47.035 --> 29:48.596
building sustainable housing
for the poor.

29:48.620 --> 29:50.111
Guess where. Sokovia.

29:54.001 --> 29:55.478
He wanted to make
a difference, I suppose.

29:55.502 --> 29:56.788
We won't know because we dropped

29:56.878 --> 29:58.995
a building on him
while we were kicking ass.

30:07.389 --> 30:09.881
There's no decision-making
process here.

30:11.601 --> 30:12.762
We need to be put in check!

30:13.061 --> 30:15.428
Whatever form that takes, I'm game.

30:15.605 --> 30:16.708
If we can't accept limitations,

30:16.732 --> 30:17.768
if we're boundary-less...

30:17.858 --> 30:19.975
we're no better than the bad guys.

30:20.068 --> 30:22.560
Tony, someone dies on your watch,
you don't give up.

30:22.863 --> 30:23.523
Who said we're giving up?

30:23.613 --> 30:26.196
We are if we're not
taking responsibility for our actions.

30:26.366 --> 30:28.153
This document just shifts the blame.

30:28.327 --> 30:29.989
I'm sorry, Steve.

30:30.162 --> 30:31.744
That is dangerously arrogant.

30:32.039 --> 30:34.031
This is the United Nations
we're talking about.

30:34.124 --> 30:36.411
It's not the World Security Council,

30:36.501 --> 30:37.895
it's not S.H.I.E.L.D., it's not HYDRA.

30:37.919 --> 30:39.205
No, but it's run by people

30:39.296 --> 30:40.662
with agendas, and agendas change.

30:40.839 --> 30:42.671
That's good. That's why I'm here.

30:42.758 --> 30:45.403
When I realised what my weapons
were capable of in the wrong hands...

30:45.427 --> 30:47.027
I shut it down
and stopped manufacturing.

30:47.262 --> 30:49.504
Tony, you chose to do that.

30:49.598 --> 30:52.511
If we sign this, we surrender
our right to choose.

30:53.518 --> 30:55.997
What if this panel sends us somewhere
we don't think we should go?

30:56.021 --> 30:57.415
What if there is somewhere
we need to go

30:57.439 --> 30:58.439
and they don't let us?

30:58.690 --> 31:00.181
We may not be perfect,

31:00.275 --> 31:01.982
but the safest hands are still our own.

31:02.152 --> 31:04.565
If we don't do this now,

31:04.654 --> 31:06.316
it's gonna be done to us later.

31:06.490 --> 31:08.402
That's the fact. That won't be pretty.

31:08.575 --> 31:09.802
You're saying they'll come for me.

31:09.826 --> 31:11.192
We would protect you.

31:11.286 --> 31:13.073
Maybe Tony's right.

31:14.373 --> 31:16.740
If we have one hand on the wheel,

31:16.833 --> 31:18.916
we can still steer. If we take it off...

31:19.002 --> 31:20.772
Aren't you the same woman
who told the government

31:20.796 --> 31:22.253
to kiss her ass a few years ago?

31:22.381 --> 31:24.714
I'm just reading the terrain.

31:25.008 --> 31:28.172
We have made some
very public mistakes.

31:28.345 --> 31:30.382
We need to win their trust back.

31:30.555 --> 31:32.672
Focus up. I'm sorry.
Did I just mishear you...

31:32.849 --> 31:34.952
- or did you agree with me?
- I want to take it back now.

31:34.976 --> 31:35.976
No, you can't retract it.

31:36.061 --> 31:37.061
Thank you. Unprecedented.

31:38.730 --> 31:41.438
Okay. Case closed. I win.

31:42.818 --> 31:43.979
I have to go.

32:26.194 --> 32:29.733
And now, I would like
to invite Sharon Carter

32:29.823 --> 32:31.405
to come up and say a few words.

32:45.088 --> 32:48.297
Margaret Carter was known to most
as a founder of S.H.I.E.L.D...

32:49.259 --> 32:51.342
but I just knew her as Aunt Peggy.

32:53.722 --> 32:55.554
She had a photograph in her office.

32:55.849 --> 32:58.842
Aunt Peggy standing next to JFK.

32:59.811 --> 33:01.552
As a kid, that was pretty cool.

33:01.855 --> 33:04.222
But it was a lot to live up to.

33:04.441 --> 33:06.728
Which is why I never told
anyone we were related.

33:08.153 --> 33:10.270
I asked her once how she managed

33:10.363 --> 33:12.229
to master diplomacy and espionage...

33:12.407 --> 33:16.742
in a time when no one wanted to see
a woman succeed at either.

33:17.245 --> 33:19.077
She said, compromise where you can.

33:19.998 --> 33:23.207
But where you can't, don't.

33:24.127 --> 33:29.623
Even if everyone is telling you
that something wrong is something right.

33:29.799 --> 33:33.042
Even if the whole world
is telling you to move...

33:33.136 --> 33:36.846
it is your duty to plant
yourself like a tree...

33:37.098 --> 33:41.513
look them in the eye and say
"No, you move."

33:53.240 --> 33:55.357
When I came out of the ice,

33:55.450 --> 33:57.817
I thought everyone
I had known was gone.

33:58.578 --> 34:00.695
Then I found out she was alive.

34:01.748 --> 34:03.284
I was just lucky to have her.

34:03.917 --> 34:05.249
She had you back, too.

34:07.837 --> 34:09.169
Who else signed?

34:10.048 --> 34:12.836
Tony, Rhodey, Vision.

34:13.760 --> 34:14.760
Clint?

34:15.554 --> 34:17.136
Says he's retired.

34:17.347 --> 34:19.134
- Wanda?
- TBD.

34:20.767 --> 34:23.475
I'm off to Vienna
for the signing of the Accords.

34:23.728 --> 34:25.264
There's plenty of room on the jet.

34:29.150 --> 34:31.984
Just because it's the path
of least resistance...

34:32.153 --> 34:34.361
doesn't mean it's the wrong path.

34:34.614 --> 34:37.402
Staying together is more important
than how we stay together.

34:38.285 --> 34:40.402
What are we giving up to do it?

34:44.624 --> 34:45.865
I'm sorry, Nat.

34:46.126 --> 34:47.788
I can't sign it.

34:49.212 --> 34:50.212
I know.

34:52.632 --> 34:54.043
Then what are you doing here?

34:56.886 --> 34:59.173
I didn't want you to be alone.

35:05.937 --> 35:07.144
Come here.

35:12.694 --> 35:15.607
<i>At a special
United Nations conference...</i>

35:15.697 --> 35:18.235
<i>117 countries have come together</i>

35:18.366 --> 35:21.029
<i>to ratify the Sokovia Accords.</i>

35:25.040 --> 35:26.497
Excuse me, Ms Romanoff?

35:26.583 --> 35:28.199
- Yes?
- These need your signature.

35:29.878 --> 35:31.210
- Thank you.
- Thanks.

35:32.339 --> 35:35.707
I suppose neither of us
is used to the spotlight.

35:37.093 --> 35:39.050
Oh, well, it's not always so flattering.

35:39.304 --> 35:41.546
You seem to be doing all right so far.

35:42.098 --> 35:44.055
Considering your last trip
to Capitol Hill...

35:44.643 --> 35:48.136
I wouldn't think you'd be particularly
comfortable in this company.

35:48.229 --> 35:49.345
Well, I'm not.

35:49.439 --> 35:52.273
And that alone makes me glad
you are here, Ms Romanoff.

35:52.442 --> 35:54.229
Why? You don't approve of all this?

35:54.319 --> 35:57.653
The Accords, yes.
The politics, not really.

35:58.156 --> 36:01.570
Two people in a room can get
more done than a hundred.

36:01.743 --> 36:04.076
Unless you need to move a piano.

36:06.623 --> 36:07.659
Ms Romanoff.

36:07.832 --> 36:08.868
King T'Chaka.

36:09.501 --> 36:11.821
Please, allow me to apologise
for what happened in Nigeria.

36:11.920 --> 36:13.456
Thank you.

36:13.630 --> 36:15.838
Thank you for agreeing to all of this.

36:16.132 --> 36:19.250
I'm sad to hear that Captain Rogers
will not be joining us today.

36:19.511 --> 36:20.718
Yes, so am I.

36:20.887 --> 36:22.344
<i>If everyone could please be seated.</i>

36:22.430 --> 36:24.171
<i>This assembly is now in session.</i>

36:25.100 --> 36:26.261
That is the future calling.

36:28.103 --> 36:29.219
Such a pleasure.

36:29.437 --> 36:30.598
Thank you.

36:31.940 --> 36:35.650
For a man
who disapproves of diplomacy,

36:36.361 --> 36:38.273
you're getting quite good at it.

36:38.863 --> 36:40.445
I'm happy, Father.

36:45.453 --> 36:46.453
Thank you.

36:47.163 --> 36:48.163
Thank you.

36:48.873 --> 36:51.286
<i>When stolen Wakandan vibranium</i>

36:51.376 --> 36:54.289
<i>was used to make a terrible weapon...</i>

36:54.379 --> 36:58.339
<i>we in Wakanda were forced
to question our legacy.</i>

36:59.008 --> 37:01.250
Those men and women
killed in Nigeria...

37:01.428 --> 37:03.340
were part of a goodwill mission

37:03.430 --> 37:05.547
from a country too long in the shadows.

37:06.766 --> 37:10.976
We will not, however,
let misfortune drive us back.

37:11.062 --> 37:14.772
We will fight to improve
the world we wish to join.

37:15.275 --> 37:19.019
I am grateful to the Avengers
for supporting this initiative.

37:21.197 --> 37:23.280
Wakanda is proud

37:23.366 --> 37:25.278
to extend its hand in peace.

37:25.452 --> 37:26.452
Everybody get down!

38:01.613 --> 38:04.356
My mom tried to
talk me out of enlisting...

38:04.532 --> 38:05.943
but, um, not Aunt Peggy.

38:06.117 --> 38:08.109
She bought me my first thigh holster.

38:08.453 --> 38:10.160
Very practical.

38:10.330 --> 38:11.696
And stylish.

38:17.462 --> 38:19.704
CIA has you stationed over here now?

38:19.881 --> 38:21.543
Berlin. Joint Terrorism Task Force.

38:22.050 --> 38:23.882
Right. Right. Sounds fun.

38:24.552 --> 38:26.009
I know, right?

38:28.723 --> 38:31.056
I've been meaning to ask you.

38:31.226 --> 38:34.139
When you were spying on me
from across the hall...

38:34.395 --> 38:35.715
You mean when I was doing my job.

38:38.608 --> 38:39.815
Did Peggy know?

38:42.403 --> 38:44.360
She kept so many secrets.

38:44.948 --> 38:46.564
I didn't want her to have one from you.

38:51.120 --> 38:52.452
Thanks for walking me back.

38:52.997 --> 38:54.204
Sure.

38:57.669 --> 38:58.830
Steve.

38:59.087 --> 39:00.703
There's something you gotta see.

39:01.047 --> 39:02.754
<i>A bomb hidden in a news van...</i>

39:02.924 --> 39:03.924
Who's coordinating?

39:04.050 --> 39:05.069
<i>Ripped through
the UN building in Vienna.</i>

39:05.093 --> 39:06.237
Good. They're solid. Forensics?

39:06.261 --> 39:07.404
<i>More than 70 people have been injured.</i>

39:07.428 --> 39:11.217
<i>At least 12 are dead,
including Wakanda's King T'Chaka.</i>

39:11.391 --> 39:13.231
<i>Officials have released
a video of a suspect...</i>

39:13.351 --> 39:15.764
<i>who they have identified
as James Buchanan Barnes...</i>

39:15.937 --> 39:17.348
<i>the Winter Soldier.</i>

39:17.522 --> 39:18.933
<i>The infamous HYDRA agent...</i>

39:19.107 --> 39:22.100
<i>linked to numerous acts of terrorism
and political assassinations.</i>

39:22.277 --> 39:23.768
I have to go to work.

39:29.534 --> 39:32.743
Call MI6, see if we can get
Micro Forensics to hurry this up.

39:32.912 --> 39:34.181
We need the whole team
here in two hours

39:34.205 --> 39:35.286
or it's not worth it.

39:45.550 --> 39:46.711
I'm very sorry.

39:53.725 --> 39:55.091
In my culture...

39:55.310 --> 39:58.144
death is not the end.

39:59.981 --> 40:03.019
It's more of a stepping-off point.

40:04.193 --> 40:05.684
You reach out with both hands...

40:05.987 --> 40:08.229
and Bast and Sekhmet,

40:08.323 --> 40:10.906
they lead you into the green veldt...

40:11.826 --> 40:13.863
where you can run forever.

40:14.746 --> 40:16.408
That sounds very peaceful.

40:17.916 --> 40:19.999
My father thought so.

40:21.920 --> 40:24.003
I am not my father.

40:24.130 --> 40:25.337
T'Challa...

40:25.840 --> 40:28.332
Task Force will decide
who brings in Barnes.

40:30.595 --> 40:32.712
Don't bother, Ms Romanoff.

40:33.681 --> 40:35.263
I'll kill him myself.

40:41.940 --> 40:42.940
Yeah?

40:43.024 --> 40:44.265
You all right?

40:44.442 --> 40:47.025
<i>Uh, yeah, thanks. I got lucky.</i>

40:53.034 --> 40:56.618
I know how much Barnes
means to you. I really do.

40:57.622 --> 41:00.615
Stay home. You'll only make this worse.

41:00.875 --> 41:02.207
<i>For all of us.</i>

41:02.502 --> 41:03.538
<i>Please.</i>

41:03.670 --> 41:04.855
Are you saying you'll arrest me?

41:04.879 --> 41:06.370
No.

41:07.340 --> 41:08.376
Someone will.

41:08.549 --> 41:10.757
<i>If you interfere.
That's how it works now.</i>

41:10.969 --> 41:14.053
If he's this far gone, Nat,
I should be the one to bring him in.

41:14.305 --> 41:15.386
<i>Why?</i>

41:15.473 --> 41:17.886
Because I'm the one
least likely to die trying.

41:19.978 --> 41:20.978
Shit.

41:25.400 --> 41:27.232
She tell you to stay out of it?

41:28.987 --> 41:29.987
Might have a point.

41:30.154 --> 41:31.270
He'd do it for me.

41:31.531 --> 41:32.942
1945, maybe.

41:33.074 --> 41:35.817
I just want to make sure
we consider all our options.

41:36.119 --> 41:37.485
The people that shoot at you

41:37.704 --> 41:39.070
usually wind up shooting at me.

41:41.666 --> 41:44.249
Tips have been pouring in
since that footage went public.

41:44.460 --> 41:46.580
Everybody thinks
the Winter Soldier goes to their gym.

41:46.921 --> 41:48.412
Most of it's noise.

41:48.631 --> 41:49.917
Except for this.

41:51.926 --> 41:54.259
My boss expects a briefing,
pretty much now...

41:54.429 --> 41:56.591
so that's all the head start
you're gonna get.

41:56.681 --> 41:57.762
Thank you.

41:57.849 --> 41:59.590
You're gonna have to hurry.

42:00.518 --> 42:02.225
We have orders to shoot on sight.

42:08.443 --> 42:11.311
<i>Homecoming</i>

42:12.989 --> 42:14.070
<i>One</i>

42:14.615 --> 42:15.615
<i>One</i>

42:20.663 --> 42:22.780
<i>Freight car</i>

42:34.052 --> 42:35.964
I have your breakfast.

42:39.682 --> 42:41.799
I could smell it before I opened the door.

42:42.018 --> 42:43.850
Side of bacon and black coffee.

42:44.020 --> 42:44.510
Again.

42:44.979 --> 42:47.062
I can make you something
different, if you like.

42:47.190 --> 42:47.930
This is wonderful...

42:48.149 --> 42:49.389
I will just put this on your...

42:49.817 --> 42:51.399
It's okay, I can manage!

44:24.745 --> 44:25.745
<i>Heads up, Cap.</i>

44:25.913 --> 44:28.246
<i>German Special Forces,
approaching from the south.</i>

44:29.041 --> 44:30.248
Understood.

44:39.010 --> 44:40.010
Do you know me?

44:42.889 --> 44:44.551
You're Steve.

44:45.433 --> 44:47.675
I read about you in a museum.

44:48.269 --> 44:50.010
<i>They've set the perimeter.</i>

44:51.063 --> 44:52.599
I know you're nervous,

44:52.690 --> 44:54.147
and you have plenty of reason to be.

44:56.110 --> 44:57.476
But you're lying.

44:58.738 --> 45:00.730
I wasn't in Vienna.
I don't do that any more.

45:00.907 --> 45:02.107
<i>They're entering the building.</i>

45:02.158 --> 45:04.741
Well, the people
who think you did are coming here now.

45:04.869 --> 45:06.656
And they're not planning
on taking you alive.

45:06.787 --> 45:08.278
That's smart.

45:08.372 --> 45:09.579
Good strategy.

45:11.250 --> 45:12.730
<i>They're on the roof. I'm compromised.</i>

45:15.838 --> 45:17.518
This doesn't have to end in a fight, Buck.

45:22.637 --> 45:24.629
- It always ends in a fight.
<i>- Five seconds.</i>

45:25.640 --> 45:27.176
You pulled me from the river.

45:27.808 --> 45:28.808
Why?

45:29.810 --> 45:31.392
- I don't know.
<i>- Three seconds.</i>

45:31.562 --> 45:33.144
Yes, you do.

45:34.649 --> 45:35.730
<i>Breach! Breach! Breach!</i>

45:56.295 --> 45:57.295
Buck, stop!

45:57.922 --> 45:59.003
You're gonna kill someone.

46:01.717 --> 46:03.049
I'm not gonna kill anyone.

46:49.390 --> 46:50.926
Suspect has broken containment!

46:51.267 --> 46:52.827
...he's headed down the east stairwell!

47:03.529 --> 47:04.529
Come on, man.

47:26.552 --> 47:27.552
Ahhh!

48:09.553 --> 48:10.964
Sam, southwest rooftop.

48:11.138 --> 48:12.424
<i>Who the hell's the other guy?</i>

48:12.515 --> 48:13.756
About to find out.

48:26.445 --> 48:28.232
- Sam.
<i>- Got him.</i>

49:09.864 --> 49:11.230
<i>Stand down!</i>

49:13.868 --> 49:14.868
<i>Stand down!</i>

49:43.898 --> 49:45.389
Sam, I can't shake this guy.

49:45.566 --> 49:46.727
Right behind you.

51:21.829 --> 51:23.866
Stand down, now.

51:31.005 --> 51:32.712
<i>Congratulations, Cap.</i>

51:33.007 --> 51:34.623
<i>You're a criminal.</i>

51:57.364 --> 51:58.571
<i>Your Highness.</i>

52:04.788 --> 52:06.996
"A pinch of paprika."

52:07.124 --> 52:08.124
A pinch.

52:11.920 --> 52:13.786
Is that paprikash?

52:13.922 --> 52:17.211
I thought it might lift your spirits.

52:30.731 --> 52:32.723
Spirits lifted.

52:34.318 --> 52:36.230
In my defence,

52:36.320 --> 52:39.154
I haven't actually ever eaten
anything before, so...

52:39.281 --> 52:40.488
May I?

52:40.574 --> 52:41.574
Please.

52:48.666 --> 52:49.907
- Wanda?
- Hmm.

52:50.417 --> 52:52.033
No one dislikes you, Wanda.

52:54.505 --> 52:55.505
Thanks.

52:55.589 --> 52:56.625
Oh, you're welcome.

52:56.840 --> 53:00.174
No, it's a involuntary response
in their amygdala.

53:00.260 --> 53:02.377
They can't help but be afraid of you.

53:02.554 --> 53:03.554
Are you?

53:03.597 --> 53:05.384
My amygdala is synthetic, so...

53:09.103 --> 53:12.267
I used to think of myself one way.

53:13.941 --> 53:15.853
But after this...

53:16.276 --> 53:18.438
I am something else.

53:18.612 --> 53:22.105
I'm still me, I think, but...

53:24.243 --> 53:26.906
that's not what everyone else sees.

53:30.040 --> 53:31.997
Do you know, I don't know what this is?

53:33.127 --> 53:34.127
Not really.

53:34.628 --> 53:36.369
I know it's not of this world...

53:36.588 --> 53:37.954
that it powered Loki's staff,

53:38.090 --> 53:40.298
gave you your abilities, but...

53:41.760 --> 53:44.969
its true nature is a mystery.

53:45.264 --> 53:47.130
And yet, it is part of me.

53:47.349 --> 53:48.465
Are you afraid of it?

53:49.309 --> 53:51.642
I wish to understand it.

53:51.812 --> 53:53.974
The more I do, the less it controls me.

53:54.148 --> 53:57.061
One day... who knows?

53:57.234 --> 53:58.475
I may even control it.

54:01.196 --> 54:05.031
I don't know what's in this
but it is not paprika.

54:05.826 --> 54:07.909
I'm gonna go to the store.

54:08.537 --> 54:10.529
I'll be back in 20 minutes.

54:10.748 --> 54:13.832
Alternatively, we could order a pizza?

54:15.002 --> 54:17.870
Vision, are you not letting me leave?

54:19.548 --> 54:21.335
It is a question of safety.

54:21.508 --> 54:23.420
I can protect myself.

54:24.845 --> 54:26.256
Not yours.

54:27.890 --> 54:30.507
Mr Stark would like to
avoid the possibility

54:30.684 --> 54:32.471
of another public incident.

54:32.853 --> 54:36.893
Until the Accords are on
a more secure foundation.

54:39.485 --> 54:41.522
And what do you want?

54:42.654 --> 54:44.145
For people to see you...

54:45.032 --> 54:46.523
as I do.

55:19.691 --> 55:20.691
So, you like cats?

55:20.859 --> 55:22.521
- Sam.
- What?

55:22.820 --> 55:25.278
Dude shows up dressed like a cat,
you don't wanna know more?

55:27.491 --> 55:29.232
Your suit... it's vibranium?

55:32.913 --> 55:35.121
The Black Panther
has been the protector

55:35.207 --> 55:37.119
of Wakanda for generations.

55:38.210 --> 55:41.499
A mantle, passed from warrior to warrior.

55:43.048 --> 55:45.791
And now, because your friend
murdered my father...

55:46.593 --> 55:49.256
I also wear the mantle of king.

55:50.097 --> 55:51.554
So, I ask you...

55:51.640 --> 55:54.633
as both warrior and king...

55:55.853 --> 55:59.597
how long do you think you can
keep your friend safe from me?

56:19.418 --> 56:20.704
What's gonna happen to him?

56:20.878 --> 56:23.086
Same thing that ought to happen to you.

56:23.171 --> 56:25.379
Psychological evaluation
and extradition.

56:25.549 --> 56:27.509
This is Everett Ross,
Deputy Task Force Commander.

56:27.968 --> 56:28.968
What about a lawyer?

56:29.136 --> 56:30.798
Lawyer. That's funny.

56:31.138 --> 56:33.095
See their weapons are placed in lockup.

56:33.265 --> 56:35.131
We'll write you a receipt.

56:35.309 --> 56:38.643
I better not look out the window
and see anybody flying around in that.

56:44.693 --> 56:46.275
You'll be
provided with an office

56:46.361 --> 56:47.727
instead of a cell.

56:47.821 --> 56:49.733
Now, do me a favour, stay in it?

56:50.490 --> 56:52.447
I don't intend on going anywhere.

56:52.618 --> 56:56.237
For the record, this is what
making things worse looks like.

56:56.538 --> 56:57.654
He's alive.

56:57.998 --> 56:59.534
No.

56:59.791 --> 57:01.999
Romania was not Accords-sanctioned.

57:02.169 --> 57:03.785
Colonel Rhodes is supervising cleanup.

57:03.962 --> 57:05.874
Try not to break anything
while we fix this.

57:06.048 --> 57:08.415
Consequences? You bet
there'll be consequences.

57:08.592 --> 57:10.208
Obviously you can quote me on that,

57:10.302 --> 57:11.821
because I just said it. Anything else?

57:11.845 --> 57:12.881
Thank you, sir.

57:14.139 --> 57:15.425
"Consequences"?

57:15.557 --> 57:17.035
Secretary Ross
wants you both prosecuted.

57:17.059 --> 57:18.345
Had to give him something.

57:18.518 --> 57:20.078
I'm not getting that shield back, am I?

57:20.437 --> 57:21.748
Technically, it's the
government's property.

57:21.772 --> 57:22.808
Wings, too.

57:22.981 --> 57:24.188
That's cold.

57:24.524 --> 57:25.765
Warmer than jail.

57:53.512 --> 57:55.595
Hey, you wanna see
something cool?

57:56.390 --> 57:58.552
I pulled something from Dad's archives.

58:00.018 --> 58:01.384
Felt timely.

58:05.399 --> 58:08.983
FDR signed the Lend-Lease bill
with these in 1941.

58:09.653 --> 58:12.566
Provided support to the Allies
when they needed it most.

58:12.739 --> 58:14.779
Some would say it brought
our country closer to war.

58:16.451 --> 58:18.864
See? If not for these,
you wouldn't be here.

58:20.497 --> 58:22.989
I'm trying to... What do you call it?

58:23.291 --> 58:25.248
That's an olive branch.

58:26.086 --> 58:27.577
Is that what you call it?

58:29.006 --> 58:31.464
Is Pepper here? I didn't see her.

58:32.718 --> 58:35.005
We're kinda...

58:35.595 --> 58:37.257
- Well, not kinda...
- Pregnant?

58:37.723 --> 58:39.214
No. Definitely not.

58:39.391 --> 58:41.178
We're taking a break.

58:41.351 --> 58:42.558
It's nobody's fault.

58:44.146 --> 58:45.603
I'm so sorry, Tony. I didn't know.

58:46.398 --> 58:49.357
A few years ago, I almost lost her,
so I trashed all my suits.

58:50.485 --> 58:52.351
Then, we had to mop up HYDRA...

58:52.529 --> 58:54.862
and then Ultron. My fault.

58:55.032 --> 58:58.241
And then, and then, and then,
I never stopped.

58:58.410 --> 59:00.777
Because the truth is I don't wanna stop.

59:02.164 --> 59:04.201
I don't wanna lose her.

59:04.374 --> 59:06.991
I thought maybe the Accords
could split the difference.

59:10.630 --> 59:12.792
In her defence, I'm a handful.

59:14.009 --> 59:16.467
Yet, Dad was a pain in the ass,

59:16.553 --> 59:18.340
but he and Mom always made it work.

59:18.513 --> 59:19.970
I'm glad Howard got married.

59:20.682 --> 59:22.639
I only knew him
when he was young and single.

59:22.809 --> 59:24.721
Oh, really? You two knew each other?

59:24.811 --> 59:26.177
He never mentioned that.

59:26.354 --> 59:28.971
Maybe only a thousand times.

59:29.608 --> 59:30.974
God, I hated you.

59:32.986 --> 59:34.602
I don't mean to make things difficult.

59:34.780 --> 59:37.067
I know, because you're
a very polite person.

59:37.699 --> 59:39.986
If I see a situation pointed south...

59:40.827 --> 59:42.318
I can't ignore it.

59:42.412 --> 59:43.778
Sometimes I wish I could.

59:43.955 --> 59:44.991
No, you don't.

59:48.126 --> 59:49.617
No, I don't.

59:50.337 --> 59:51.337
Sometimes...

59:51.505 --> 59:54.543
Sometimes I wanna
punch you in your perfect teeth.

59:55.133 --> 59:56.590
But I don't wanna see you gone.

59:57.344 --> 59:58.835
We need you, Cap.

59:59.554 --> 01:00:03.013
So far, nothing's happened
that can't be undone, if you sign.

01:00:03.433 --> 01:00:05.299
We can make the last 24 hours legit.

01:00:05.477 --> 01:00:07.685
Barnes gets transferred to
an American psych-centre...

01:00:07.854 --> 01:00:09.811
instead of a Wakandan prison.

01:00:21.660 --> 01:00:22.992
I'm not saying it's impossible...

01:00:23.203 --> 01:00:25.195
but there would have to be safeguards.

01:00:25.372 --> 01:00:26.408
Sure.

01:00:26.623 --> 01:00:28.285
Once we put out the PR fire,

01:00:28.375 --> 01:00:30.367
those documents can be amended.

01:00:30.544 --> 01:00:32.438
I'd file a motion to have
you and Wanda reinstated...

01:00:32.462 --> 01:00:34.294
Wanda? What about Wanda?

01:00:34.589 --> 01:00:36.275
She's fine. She's confined
to the compound, currently.

01:00:36.299 --> 01:00:37.506
Vision's keeping her company.

01:00:37.676 --> 01:00:38.676
Oh, God, Tony.

01:00:38.844 --> 01:00:41.177
Every time I think you see
things the right way...

01:00:41.346 --> 01:00:42.406
It's 100 acres with a lap pool.

01:00:42.430 --> 01:00:43.470
It's got a screening room.

01:00:43.557 --> 01:00:44.784
There's worse ways to protect people.

01:00:44.808 --> 01:00:45.844
Protection?

01:00:46.560 --> 01:00:47.641
Is that how you see this?

01:00:47.727 --> 01:00:49.764
This is protection? It's internment, Tony.

01:00:49.938 --> 01:00:51.332
- She's not a US citizen.
- Oh, come on, Tony.

01:00:51.356 --> 01:00:52.917
And they don't grant visas
to weapons of mass destruction.

01:00:52.941 --> 01:00:53.941
She's a kid!

01:00:54.025 --> 01:00:55.391
Give me a break!

01:00:56.611 --> 01:00:58.648
I'm doing what has to be done.

01:00:58.822 --> 01:01:00.609
To stave off something worse.

01:01:03.660 --> 01:01:05.526
You keep telling yourself that.

01:01:08.665 --> 01:01:09.951
Hate to break up the set.

01:01:17.424 --> 01:01:19.290
<i>Hello, Mr Barnes.</i>

01:01:19.968 --> 01:01:22.335
<i>I've been sent by
the United Nations to evaluate you.</i>

01:01:22.512 --> 01:01:24.720
<i>Do you mind if I sit?</i>

01:01:29.644 --> 01:01:31.351
<i>Your first name is James?</i>

01:01:32.856 --> 01:01:34.768
The receipt for your gear.

01:01:36.610 --> 01:01:38.272
"Bird costume"? Come on.

01:01:38.445 --> 01:01:40.152
I didn't write it.

01:01:46.161 --> 01:01:47.743
<i>I'm not here to judge you.</i>

01:01:48.205 --> 01:01:49.765
<i>I just want to ask you a few questions.</i>

01:01:51.458 --> 01:01:53.700
<i>Do you know where you are, James?</i>

01:01:56.880 --> 01:01:59.588
<i>I can't help you if you
don't talk to me, James.</i>

01:02:00.550 --> 01:02:02.166
<i>My name is Bucky.</i>

01:02:11.144 --> 01:02:12.635
Hello?

01:02:19.736 --> 01:02:20.817
Hey!

01:02:41.258 --> 01:02:44.001
Why would the Task Force
release this photo to begin with?

01:02:44.386 --> 01:02:46.673
Get the word out,
involve as many eyes as we can?

01:02:46.846 --> 01:02:49.714
Right. It's a good way
to flush a guy out of hiding.

01:02:49.891 --> 01:02:51.883
Set off a bomb, get your picture taken.

01:02:52.060 --> 01:02:54.247
Get seven billion people looking
for the Winter Soldier.

01:02:54.271 --> 01:02:56.103
You're saying someone
framed him to find him?

01:02:56.273 --> 01:02:57.333
Steve, we looked
for the guy for two years

01:02:57.357 --> 01:02:58.393
and found nothing.

01:02:58.525 --> 01:03:00.517
We didn't bomb the UN.
That turns a lot of heads.

01:03:00.610 --> 01:03:01.942
Yeah, but that doesn't guarantee

01:03:02.028 --> 01:03:03.256
that whoever framed him would get him.

01:03:03.280 --> 01:03:05.112
It guarantees that we would.

01:03:11.204 --> 01:03:12.204
Yeah.

01:03:14.958 --> 01:03:16.369
Tell me, Bucky.

01:03:16.710 --> 01:03:19.077
You've seen a great deal, haven't you?

01:03:20.463 --> 01:03:22.546
<i>I don't wanna talk about it.</i>

01:03:23.216 --> 01:03:25.833
You fear that if you open your mouth,

01:03:25.927 --> 01:03:27.714
the horrors might never stop.

01:03:31.391 --> 01:03:32.472
Don't worry.

01:03:35.603 --> 01:03:37.890
We only have to talk about one.

01:04:02.130 --> 01:04:04.087
Come on, guys, get me eyes on Barnes.

01:04:04.924 --> 01:04:07.507
Friday, get me a source on that outage.

01:04:08.803 --> 01:04:10.920
Sub-level five, East Wing.

01:04:14.351 --> 01:04:15.808
What the hell is this?

01:04:15.977 --> 01:04:17.593
Why don't we discuss your home?

01:04:17.771 --> 01:04:20.809
Not Romania.
Certainly not Brooklyn, no.

01:04:21.858 --> 01:04:25.351
I mean your real home.

01:04:31.451 --> 01:04:32.737
<i>Longing</i>

01:04:33.453 --> 01:04:34.453
No.

01:04:35.914 --> 01:04:36.620
<i>Rusted</i>

01:04:36.831 --> 01:04:38.072
Stop.

01:04:38.458 --> 01:04:39.458
<i>Se venteen</i>

01:04:41.795 --> 01:04:42.795
Stop.

01:04:45.173 --> 01:04:46.173
<i>Daybreak</i>

01:04:52.430 --> 01:04:53.430
<i>Furnace</i>

01:04:55.975 --> 01:04:56.975
<i>Nine</i>

01:05:00.021 --> 01:05:01.228
<i>Benign</i>

01:05:04.651 --> 01:05:06.267
<i>Homecoming</i>

01:05:07.028 --> 01:05:08.028
<i>One</i>

01:05:09.489 --> 01:05:10.489
<i>Freight car</i>

01:05:27.048 --> 01:05:28.164
Soldier?

01:05:31.136 --> 01:05:32.377
Ready to comply.

01:05:33.221 --> 01:05:38.592
Mission report. December 16, 1991.

01:05:49.279 --> 01:05:50.611
Help me.

01:05:51.239 --> 01:05:52.239
Help.

01:05:55.243 --> 01:05:56.243
Get up.

01:05:59.706 --> 01:06:01.538
Who are you? What do you want?

01:06:02.917 --> 01:06:04.909
To see an empire fall.

01:06:37.076 --> 01:06:38.076
Hey.

01:06:44.792 --> 01:06:46.158
Evac all civilians.

01:06:46.336 --> 01:06:48.731
Get me a perimeter around the building,
and gunships in the air.

01:06:48.755 --> 01:06:50.246
Please tell me you brought a suit.

01:06:50.423 --> 01:06:52.881
Sure did. It's a lovely Tom Ford,
three-piece, two-button.

01:06:53.009 --> 01:06:54.500
I'm an active-duty non-combatant.

01:06:55.136 --> 01:06:56.502
Follow me.

01:07:13.321 --> 01:07:14.321
<i>We're in position.</i>

01:07:46.896 --> 01:07:48.808
You could at least recognise me.

01:08:41.951 --> 01:08:43.158
Damn it.

01:10:20.466 --> 01:10:22.674
<i>He asked me again
if you were going to be there.</i>

01:10:22.760 --> 01:10:24.717
<i>I said I wasn't sure.</i>

01:10:24.804 --> 01:10:27.638
<i>You should have seen his
little face. Just try, okay?</i>

01:10:28.307 --> 01:10:30.048
<i>I'm going to bed.</i>

01:10:30.226 --> 01:10:31.637
<i>I love you.</i>

01:10:35.523 --> 01:10:39.517
James Barnes the suspect
in the UN Vienna bombing...

01:10:39.652 --> 01:10:41.143
...escaped custody today.

01:10:41.404 --> 01:10:44.363
...also missing Avenger
Captain Steve Rogers...

01:10:44.490 --> 01:10:45.490
and Sam Wilson.

01:11:09.515 --> 01:11:10.515
Hey, Cap!

01:11:23.321 --> 01:11:24.402
Steve.

01:11:25.406 --> 01:11:27.614
Which Bucky am I talking to?

01:11:29.243 --> 01:11:31.326
Your mom's name was Sarah.

01:11:35.458 --> 01:11:38.701
You used to wear newspapers
in your shoes.

01:11:40.129 --> 01:11:41.336
Can't read that in a museum.

01:11:41.506 --> 01:11:43.213
Just like that,
we're supposed to be cool?

01:11:43.591 --> 01:11:45.002
What did I do?

01:11:45.134 --> 01:11:45.874
Enough.

01:11:46.052 --> 01:11:47.839
Oh, God, I knew this would happen.

01:11:48.012 --> 01:11:50.299
Everything HYDRA
put inside me is still there.

01:11:50.556 --> 01:11:52.388
All he had to do
was say the goddamn words.

01:11:52.600 --> 01:11:54.216
- Who was he?
- I don't know.

01:11:54.393 --> 01:11:56.350
People are dead.
The bombing, the setup...

01:11:56.562 --> 01:11:58.895
the doctor did all that just
to get 10 minutes with you.

01:11:59.148 --> 01:12:00.889
I need you to do
better than "I don't know."

01:12:04.612 --> 01:12:07.229
He wanted to know about Siberia.

01:12:09.909 --> 01:12:11.616
Where I was kept.

01:12:13.412 --> 01:12:15.153
He wanted to know exactly where.

01:12:15.414 --> 01:12:17.622
Why would he need to know that?

01:12:19.710 --> 01:12:22.043
Because I'm not the only Winter Soldier.

01:13:15.766 --> 01:13:17.382
It hurts!

01:13:55.014 --> 01:13:56.175
Good work.

01:14:07.360 --> 01:14:08.726
Get me out of here.

01:14:22.750 --> 01:14:23.866
Who were they?

01:14:24.043 --> 01:14:25.625
Their most elite death squad.

01:14:25.795 --> 01:14:27.878
More kills than anyone
in HYDRA history.

01:14:28.047 --> 01:14:29.333
And that was before the serum.

01:14:29.507 --> 01:14:30.623
They all turn out like you?

01:14:30.800 --> 01:14:31.881
Worse.

01:14:32.510 --> 01:14:34.297
The doctor, could he control them?

01:14:35.262 --> 01:14:36.673
Enough.

01:14:36.847 --> 01:14:38.679
Said he wanted to see an empire fall.

01:14:38.933 --> 01:14:40.549
With these guys, he could do it.

01:14:40.851 --> 01:14:43.184
They speak 30 languages,
can hide in plain sight...

01:14:43.270 --> 01:14:45.478
infiltrate, assassinate, destabilise.

01:14:45.564 --> 01:14:47.100
They can take a whole country down

01:14:47.191 --> 01:14:48.831
in one night,
you'd never see them coming.

01:14:51.362 --> 01:14:53.399
This would have been
a lot easier a week ago.

01:14:53.990 --> 01:14:56.107
- If we call Tony...
- No, he won't believe us.

01:14:56.200 --> 01:14:57.200
Even if he did...

01:14:57.284 --> 01:14:59.071
Who knows if the Accords
would let him help.

01:15:00.538 --> 01:15:01.538
We're on our own.

01:15:02.957 --> 01:15:03.957
Maybe not.

01:15:05.876 --> 01:15:07.412
I know a guy.

01:15:08.379 --> 01:15:11.338
I don't suppose you have
any idea where they are?

01:15:11.424 --> 01:15:12.424
We will.

01:15:12.591 --> 01:15:14.173
GSG 9's got the borders covered.

01:15:14.260 --> 01:15:16.047
Recon's flying 24/7.

01:15:16.220 --> 01:15:17.711
They'll get a hit. We'll handle it.

01:15:17.805 --> 01:15:19.765
You don't get it, Stark.
It's not yours to handle.

01:15:19.890 --> 01:15:22.223
It's clear you can't be objective.

01:15:22.393 --> 01:15:23.884
I'm putting Special Ops on this.

01:15:23.978 --> 01:15:25.205
What happens
when the shooting starts?

01:15:25.229 --> 01:15:26.515
What, do you kill Steve Rogers?

01:15:26.605 --> 01:15:27.937
If we're provoked.

01:15:28.107 --> 01:15:31.396
Barnes would've been eliminated
in Romania if it wasn't for Rogers.

01:15:31.569 --> 01:15:35.358
There are dead people
who would be alive now.

01:15:36.449 --> 01:15:38.281
Feel free to check my math.

01:15:38.492 --> 01:15:39.886
All due respect,
you're not gonna solve this

01:15:39.910 --> 01:15:41.151
with boys and bullets, Ross.

01:15:41.245 --> 01:15:42.485
You gotta let us bring them in.

01:15:42.705 --> 01:15:44.665
How would that end
any differently than last time?

01:15:44.790 --> 01:15:45.790
Because this time,

01:15:45.833 --> 01:15:47.553
I won't be wearing loafers
and a silk shirt.

01:15:48.794 --> 01:15:50.660
72 hours, guaranteed.

01:15:50.838 --> 01:15:52.670
36 hours.

01:15:54.216 --> 01:15:55.502
Barnes.

01:15:57.011 --> 01:15:58.343
Rogers.

01:15:59.138 --> 01:16:00.138
Wilson.

01:16:00.181 --> 01:16:01.968
Thank you, sir.

01:16:05.603 --> 01:16:07.469
My left arm is numb. Is that normal?

01:16:10.941 --> 01:16:12.022
You all right?

01:16:12.193 --> 01:16:13.274
Always.

01:16:17.364 --> 01:16:19.606
36 hours. Jeez.

01:16:19.784 --> 01:16:21.821
We're seriously understaffed.

01:16:21.994 --> 01:16:23.155
Oh, yeah.

01:16:23.329 --> 01:16:26.288
It'd be great if we had
a Hulk right about now. Any shot?

01:16:28.250 --> 01:16:30.867
You really think he'd be on our side?

01:16:31.045 --> 01:16:32.081
No.

01:16:32.254 --> 01:16:33.540
I have an idea.

01:16:33.714 --> 01:16:36.001
Me, too. Where's yours?

01:16:36.217 --> 01:16:38.004
Downstairs.

01:16:38.177 --> 01:16:39.338
Where's yours?

01:17:01.325 --> 01:17:02.691
Hey, May.

01:17:02.868 --> 01:17:04.029
Mmm. Hey.

01:17:06.163 --> 01:17:07.904
How was school today?

01:17:08.082 --> 01:17:09.323
It was okay.

01:17:09.500 --> 01:17:11.787
This crazy car parked outside.

01:17:15.297 --> 01:17:17.254
- Oh, Mr Parker.
- Um...

01:17:19.260 --> 01:17:21.297
What are you doing...

01:17:21.470 --> 01:17:23.257
Hey! Uh, I'm Peter.

01:17:23.430 --> 01:17:24.671
Tony.

01:17:25.182 --> 01:17:26.718
What are you doing here?

01:17:26.892 --> 01:17:28.178
It's about time we met.

01:17:28.269 --> 01:17:29.976
You've been getting my emails, right?

01:17:30.187 --> 01:17:31.769
- Yeah. Yeah.
- Right?

01:17:31.981 --> 01:17:32.981
Regarding the...

01:17:33.065 --> 01:17:34.209
You didn't even tell me about the grant.

01:17:34.233 --> 01:17:35.877
- About the grant.
- The September Foundation.

01:17:35.901 --> 01:17:36.901
- Right.
- Yeah.

01:17:36.944 --> 01:17:37.984
Remember when you applied?

01:17:38.070 --> 01:17:39.106
Yeah.

01:17:39.280 --> 01:17:41.772
I approved, so now we're in business.

01:17:42.408 --> 01:17:44.488
But you didn't tell me anything.
What's up with that?

01:17:44.618 --> 01:17:45.762
You keeping secrets from me now?

01:17:45.786 --> 01:17:49.575
I just know how much you love surprises
so I thought I would let you know...

01:17:50.249 --> 01:17:51.740
Anyway, what did I apply for?

01:17:51.917 --> 01:17:53.061
That's what I'm here to hash out.

01:17:53.085 --> 01:17:54.451
Okay. Hash it out, okay.

01:17:54.545 --> 01:17:57.162
It's so hard for me to believe
that she's someone's aunt.

01:17:57.339 --> 01:17:59.581
Yeah, well, we come in
all shapes and sizes, you know?

01:18:00.050 --> 01:18:02.212
This walnut date loaf is exceptional.

01:18:02.511 --> 01:18:03.905
- Let me just stop you there.
- Yeah.

01:18:03.929 --> 01:18:07.718
Is this grant got money
involved or whatever? No?

01:18:07.892 --> 01:18:09.133
Yeah, it's pretty well funded.

01:18:09.226 --> 01:18:10.387
Yeah? Wow.

01:18:10.477 --> 01:18:12.093
Look who you're talking to.

01:18:12.271 --> 01:18:14.308
- Can I have five minutes with him?
- Sure.

01:18:20.237 --> 01:18:23.526
As walnut date loaves go,
that wasn't bad.

01:18:24.825 --> 01:18:27.613
Whoa, what have we here?
Retro tech, huh?

01:18:27.828 --> 01:18:29.569
Thrift store? Salvation Army?

01:18:29.788 --> 01:18:31.850
- Uh, the garbage, actually.
- You're a dumpster diver?

01:18:31.874 --> 01:18:32.955
Yeah, I was...

01:18:33.042 --> 01:18:34.499
Anyway, look, um,

01:18:34.585 --> 01:18:36.305
I definitely did not apply
for your grant...

01:18:36.378 --> 01:18:37.914
- Ah-ah! Me first.
- Okay.

01:18:38.005 --> 01:18:40.497
Quick question of the rhetorical variety.

01:18:41.842 --> 01:18:43.799
That's you, right?

01:18:44.178 --> 01:18:45.178
Um, no.

01:18:45.346 --> 01:18:46.803
- What do you mean?
- Yeah.

01:18:47.806 --> 01:18:49.422
Look at you go.

01:18:49.600 --> 01:18:52.718
Wow! Nice catch.
3,000 pounds, 40 miles an hour.

01:18:52.895 --> 01:18:55.638
That's not easy. You got mad skills.

01:18:55.898 --> 01:18:57.730
That's all on YouTube, though, right?

01:18:57.816 --> 01:18:59.307
That's where you found that?

01:18:59.485 --> 01:19:00.587
Because you know that's all fake.

01:19:00.611 --> 01:19:01.811
It's all done on the computer.

01:19:01.862 --> 01:19:02.898
Mmm-hmm.

01:19:02.988 --> 01:19:05.071
It's like that video. What is it?

01:19:05.241 --> 01:19:07.121
Yeah. Oh, you mean like
those UFOs over Phoenix?

01:19:07.201 --> 01:19:08.201
Exactly.

01:19:08.535 --> 01:19:09.821
Oh, what have we here?

01:19:11.205 --> 01:19:12.912
Uh...

01:19:18.963 --> 01:19:20.795
You're the Spider-ling.

01:19:20.965 --> 01:19:22.831
Crime-fighting spider.
You're Spider-Boy?

01:19:25.678 --> 01:19:27.260
Spider-Man.

01:19:27.638 --> 01:19:29.470
Not in that onesie, you're not.

01:19:30.015 --> 01:19:31.927
It's not a onesie.

01:19:33.352 --> 01:19:34.704
I don't believe this.
I was actually having

01:19:34.728 --> 01:19:36.515
a really good day today, Mr Stark.

01:19:36.689 --> 01:19:39.853
Didn't miss my train, this perfectly good
DVD player was just sitting there...

01:19:40.484 --> 01:19:43.101
and Algebra test, nailed it.

01:19:43.904 --> 01:19:45.361
Who else knows? Anybody?

01:19:46.949 --> 01:19:48.065
Nobody.

01:19:48.450 --> 01:19:50.442
Not even your unusually attractive aunt?

01:19:50.619 --> 01:19:51.905
No. No.

01:19:52.079 --> 01:19:54.662
No! If she knew, she would freak out.

01:19:54.832 --> 01:19:56.539
And when she freaks out, I freak out.

01:19:56.834 --> 01:19:58.834
You know what I think
is really cool? This webbing.

01:20:00.129 --> 01:20:02.496
That tensile strength is off the charts.

01:20:02.589 --> 01:20:03.955
Who manufactured that?

01:20:04.258 --> 01:20:05.465
I did.

01:20:06.552 --> 01:20:08.134
Climbing walls, how you doing that?

01:20:08.304 --> 01:20:09.545
Adhesive gloves?

01:20:09.722 --> 01:20:11.008
It's a long story. I was...

01:20:11.640 --> 01:20:13.848
Lordy! Can you even see in these?

01:20:14.018 --> 01:20:15.018
Yes, I can.

01:20:15.185 --> 01:20:16.346
I'm blind!

01:20:17.313 --> 01:20:18.895
I can see in those.

01:20:19.064 --> 01:20:19.895
Okay?

01:20:20.065 --> 01:20:22.398
It's just that when whatever
happened, happened...

01:20:22.484 --> 01:20:24.771
it's like my senses
have been dialled to 11.

01:20:25.321 --> 01:20:29.611
There's way too much input,
so they just kinda help me focus.

01:20:29.908 --> 01:20:32.195
You're in dire need of an upgrade.

01:20:32.286 --> 01:20:34.653
Systemic, top to bottom,
hundred-point restoration.

01:20:34.747 --> 01:20:35.863
That's why I'm here.

01:20:38.792 --> 01:20:39.908
Why you doing this?

01:20:41.337 --> 01:20:42.498
I gotta know, what's your MO?

01:20:42.588 --> 01:20:44.508
What gets you outta that
twin bed in the morning?

01:20:45.132 --> 01:20:46.339
Because...

01:20:50.387 --> 01:20:52.344
Because I've been me my whole life,

01:20:52.431 --> 01:20:54.093
and I've had these powers
for six months.

01:20:54.558 --> 01:20:55.719
Mmm-hmm.

01:20:55.809 --> 01:20:58.176
I read books, I build computers.

01:20:59.396 --> 01:21:02.059
Yeah, I would love to play football,

01:21:02.149 --> 01:21:03.749
but I couldn't then, so I shouldn't now.

01:21:03.942 --> 01:21:05.433
Sure, because you're different.

01:21:05.611 --> 01:21:08.524
Exactly. But I can't tell
anybody that, so I'm not.

01:21:12.242 --> 01:21:16.532
When you can do the things
that I can, but you don't...

01:21:18.957 --> 01:21:21.074
and then the bad things happen...

01:21:21.835 --> 01:21:23.451
they happen because of you.

01:21:28.133 --> 01:21:30.716
So you wanna look out for the little guy,
you wanna do your part?

01:21:30.886 --> 01:21:33.094
Make the world
a better place, all that, right?

01:21:33.347 --> 01:21:35.885
Yeah, just looking out for the little guy.

01:21:36.892 --> 01:21:38.474
That's what it is.

01:21:45.734 --> 01:21:47.896
I'm gonna sit here, so you move the leg.

01:21:56.829 --> 01:21:58.036
You got a passport?

01:21:58.122 --> 01:21:59.641
No, I don't even have a driver's licence.

01:21:59.665 --> 01:22:01.122
- You ever been to Germany?
- No.

01:22:01.208 --> 01:22:02.208
Oh, you'll love it.

01:22:02.418 --> 01:22:04.330
- I can't go to Germany.
- Why?

01:22:06.797 --> 01:22:08.004
I got homework.

01:22:08.674 --> 01:22:10.586
I'm gonna pretend you didn't say that.

01:22:10.843 --> 01:22:12.904
No, I'm being serious.
I can't just drop out of school.

01:22:12.928 --> 01:22:14.048
Might be a little dangerous.

01:22:14.096 --> 01:22:16.256
Better tell Aunt Hottie
I'm taking you on a field trip.

01:22:18.809 --> 01:22:20.641
Don't tell Aunt May.

01:22:21.478 --> 01:22:22.559
All right, Spider-Man.

01:22:26.191 --> 01:22:27.398
Get me out of this.

01:22:27.568 --> 01:22:28.604
Sorry. I'll get the...

01:22:41.540 --> 01:22:42.781
What is it?

01:22:42.958 --> 01:22:44.369
Stay here, please.

01:22:51.008 --> 01:22:52.499
Guess I shoulda knocked.

01:22:52.843 --> 01:22:56.086
Oh, my God! What are you doing here?

01:22:56.263 --> 01:22:58.550
Disappointing my kids.

01:23:02.102 --> 01:23:03.843
I'm supposed to go waterskiing.

01:23:04.354 --> 01:23:06.141
Cap needs our help. Come on.

01:23:06.482 --> 01:23:07.482
Clint!

01:23:09.401 --> 01:23:10.687
You should not be here.

01:23:13.030 --> 01:23:14.271
Really?

01:23:14.781 --> 01:23:17.865
I retire for, what, like five minutes,
and it all goes to shit.

01:23:18.118 --> 01:23:20.326
Please consider
the consequences of your actions.

01:23:20.496 --> 01:23:21.496
Okay, they're considered.

01:23:22.873 --> 01:23:24.364
Okay, we gotta go.

01:23:28.754 --> 01:23:30.040
It's this way.

01:23:30.506 --> 01:23:32.418
I've caused enough problems.

01:23:36.970 --> 01:23:38.461
You gotta help me, Wanda.

01:23:38.639 --> 01:23:40.492
Look, you wanna mope,
you can go to high school.

01:23:40.516 --> 01:23:42.553
You wanna make amends,
you get off your ass.

01:23:43.560 --> 01:23:44.560
Shit.

01:23:51.151 --> 01:23:52.892
I knew I should've stretched.

01:24:06.500 --> 01:24:08.992
Clint, you can't overpower me.

01:24:09.169 --> 01:24:11.001
I know I can't.

01:24:11.588 --> 01:24:13.170
But she can.

01:24:14.716 --> 01:24:17.800
Vision, that's enough. Let him go.

01:24:18.720 --> 01:24:19.720
I'm leaving.

01:24:19.846 --> 01:24:20.962
I can't let you.

01:24:26.019 --> 01:24:27.351
I'm sorry.

01:24:30.857 --> 01:24:32.689
If you do this...

01:24:33.151 --> 01:24:36.144
they will never stop being afraid of you.

01:24:37.614 --> 01:24:40.948
I can't control their fear, only my own.

01:24:53.171 --> 01:24:54.412
Oh...

01:24:56.341 --> 01:24:58.799
Come on. We got one more stop.

01:24:59.636 --> 01:25:01.343
It's just a matter of time.

01:25:01.430 --> 01:25:04.173
Our satellites are running
facial, biometric,

01:25:04.266 --> 01:25:05.882
and behavioural pattern scans.

01:25:10.063 --> 01:25:12.601
Move or you will be moved.

01:25:13.900 --> 01:25:16.563
As entertaining as that would be...

01:25:16.737 --> 01:25:18.899
You really think you can find him?

01:25:19.406 --> 01:25:21.068
My resources are considerable.

01:25:21.241 --> 01:25:23.608
Yeah, it took the world
70 years to find Barnes...

01:25:23.702 --> 01:25:26.194
so you could probably do that
in about half the time.

01:25:27.414 --> 01:25:29.076
You know where they are.

01:25:29.249 --> 01:25:31.332
I know someone who does.

01:25:34.087 --> 01:25:36.625
Not sure you understand
the concept of a getaway car.

01:25:36.715 --> 01:25:37.715
It's low profile.

01:25:38.342 --> 01:25:41.085
Good, because this stuff
tends to draw a crowd.

01:25:42.929 --> 01:25:44.420
Can you move your seat up?

01:25:44.598 --> 01:25:45.714
No.

01:25:45.974 --> 01:25:47.010
I owe you again.

01:25:47.643 --> 01:25:49.225
Keeping a list.

01:25:52.356 --> 01:25:54.097
You know, he kinda tried to kill me.

01:25:55.025 --> 01:25:57.733
Sorry. I'll put it on the list, too.

01:26:01.073 --> 01:26:03.281
They're going to come looking for you.

01:26:03.367 --> 01:26:04.367
I know.

01:26:07.162 --> 01:26:08.528
Thank you, Sharon.

01:26:24.096 --> 01:26:25.096
That was...

01:26:25.263 --> 01:26:26.174
Late.

01:26:26.264 --> 01:26:27.264
Damn right.

01:26:31.770 --> 01:26:32.770
I should go.

01:26:32.938 --> 01:26:33.938
Okay.

01:26:58.505 --> 01:26:59.666
Cap.

01:26:59.840 --> 01:27:02.110
You know I wouldn't have called
if I had any other choice.

01:27:02.134 --> 01:27:03.534
Hey, man, you're doing me a favour.

01:27:03.677 --> 01:27:06.010
Besides, I owe a debt.

01:27:06.179 --> 01:27:07.715
Thanks for having my back.

01:27:07.889 --> 01:27:09.380
It was time to get off my ass.

01:27:09.975 --> 01:27:11.591
How about our other recruit?

01:27:11.768 --> 01:27:13.350
He's rarin' to go.

01:27:14.146 --> 01:27:15.586
Had to put a little coffee in him...

01:27:16.690 --> 01:27:17.806
but he should be good.

01:27:21.194 --> 01:27:22.685
What time zone is this?

01:27:22.863 --> 01:27:24.695
Come on. Come on.

01:27:27.826 --> 01:27:29.738
- Captain America!
- Mr Lang.

01:27:30.829 --> 01:27:31.829
It's an honour.

01:27:32.372 --> 01:27:34.079
I'm shaking your hand too long.

01:27:34.249 --> 01:27:35.490
Wow! This is awesome!

01:27:35.709 --> 01:27:38.292
Captain America.
I know you, too. You're great!

01:27:42.048 --> 01:27:43.048
Jeez.

01:27:43.216 --> 01:27:45.003
Ah, look, I wanna say,

01:27:45.093 --> 01:27:47.176
I know you know
a lot of super people, so...

01:27:48.138 --> 01:27:49.970
thinks for thanking of me.

01:27:50.223 --> 01:27:51.930
- Hey, man!
- What's up, Tic Tac?

01:27:52.184 --> 01:27:53.184
Uh, good to see you.

01:27:53.268 --> 01:27:54.828
Look, what happened last time when I...

01:27:54.936 --> 01:27:58.054
It was a great audition,
but it'll never happen again.

01:27:58.356 --> 01:28:00.518
They tell you what we're up against?

01:28:00.817 --> 01:28:03.901
Something about
some psycho-assassins?

01:28:04.362 --> 01:28:06.274
We're outside the law on this one.

01:28:06.364 --> 01:28:08.321
So if you come with us,
you're a wanted man.

01:28:08.867 --> 01:28:10.278
Yeah, well, what else is new?

01:28:10.535 --> 01:28:11.535
We should get moving.

01:28:11.578 --> 01:28:13.285
We got a chopper lined up.

01:28:17.918 --> 01:28:19.705
They're evacuating the airport.

01:28:19.878 --> 01:28:20.959
Stark.

01:28:21.046 --> 01:28:22.046
Stark?

01:28:23.507 --> 01:28:25.089
Suit up.

01:28:45.737 --> 01:28:47.882
<i>Wow, it's so weird
how you run into people at the airport.</i>

01:28:47.906 --> 01:28:49.592
- Don't you think that's weird?
<i>- Definitely weird.</i>

01:28:49.616 --> 01:28:50.902
Hear me out, Tony.

01:28:50.992 --> 01:28:54.030
That doctor, the psychiatrist,
he's behind all of this.

01:28:57.415 --> 01:28:58.496
<i>Captain.</i>

01:28:58.667 --> 01:28:59.667
Your Highness.

01:29:00.168 --> 01:29:01.168
Anyway...

01:29:01.586 --> 01:29:03.623
Ross gave me 36 hours to bring you in.

01:29:03.797 --> 01:29:06.710
That was 24 hours ago.
Can you help a brother out?

01:29:06.967 --> 01:29:08.299
You're after the wrong guy.

01:29:08.510 --> 01:29:10.422
Your judgement is askew.

01:29:11.096 --> 01:29:13.136
Your old war buddy killed
innocent people yesterday.

01:29:13.306 --> 01:29:16.094
And there are five more
super soldiers just like him.

01:29:16.184 --> 01:29:18.642
I can't let the doctor
find them first, Tony. I can't.

01:29:18.937 --> 01:29:19.973
Steve...

01:29:21.022 --> 01:29:23.014
you know what's about to happen.

01:29:23.108 --> 01:29:25.441
Do you really wanna
punch your way out of this one?

01:29:29.656 --> 01:29:31.522
All right, I've run out of patience.

01:29:31.616 --> 01:29:32.616
Underoos!

01:29:38.582 --> 01:29:40.414
- Nice job, kid.
- Thanks.

01:29:40.500 --> 01:29:42.478
I could have stuck the landing
a little better, it's just...

01:29:42.502 --> 01:29:44.334
New suit. It's nothing, Mr Stark.

01:29:44.504 --> 01:29:45.620
It's perfect. Thank you.

01:29:45.797 --> 01:29:47.608
Yeah, we don't really need
to start a conversation.

01:29:47.632 --> 01:29:48.713
Okay. Cap. Captain.

01:29:49.968 --> 01:29:51.129
Big fan. I'm Spider-Man.

01:29:51.386 --> 01:29:52.405
Yeah, we'll talk about it later.

01:29:52.429 --> 01:29:54.216
- Hey, everyone.
- Good job.

01:29:54.723 --> 01:29:55.723
You've been busy.

01:29:55.891 --> 01:29:57.928
And you've been a complete idiot.

01:29:58.018 --> 01:29:59.018
Dragging in Clint...

01:29:59.144 --> 01:30:00.601
"Rescuing" Wanda from a place

01:30:00.687 --> 01:30:02.804
she doesn't even want
to leave, a safe place.

01:30:02.981 --> 01:30:04.222
I'm trying to keep...

01:30:05.525 --> 01:30:08.518
I'm trying to keep you from
tearing the Avengers apart.

01:30:09.112 --> 01:30:11.320
You did that when you signed.

01:30:12.324 --> 01:30:13.485
All right, we're done.

01:30:14.200 --> 01:30:15.691
You're gonna turn Barnes over,

01:30:15.785 --> 01:30:17.947
you're gonna come with us,
now, because it's us...

01:30:18.496 --> 01:30:19.862
or a squad of J-SOC guys...

01:30:20.165 --> 01:30:22.657
with no compunction
about being impolite.

01:30:24.669 --> 01:30:25.830
Come on.

01:30:27.005 --> 01:30:28.541
<i>We found it.</i>

01:30:29.841 --> 01:30:31.924
Their Quinjet's in
hangar five, north runway.

01:30:36.139 --> 01:30:37.425
All right, Lang.

01:30:38.516 --> 01:30:40.257
Hey, guys, something...

01:30:40.685 --> 01:30:41.805
Whoa.
What the hell was that?

01:30:41.853 --> 01:30:43.845
<i>I believe this is yours, Captain America.</i>

01:30:44.022 --> 01:30:45.022
Oh, great.

01:30:45.190 --> 01:30:46.500
All right, there's two
on the parking deck.

01:30:46.524 --> 01:30:48.085
One of them's Maximoff,
I'm gonna grab her.

01:30:48.109 --> 01:30:49.520
<i>Rhodey, you wanna take Cap?</i>

01:30:49.736 --> 01:30:51.728
<i>Got two in the terminal,
Wilson and Barnes.</i>

01:30:51.905 --> 01:30:52.905
<i>Barnes is mine.</i>

01:30:54.282 --> 01:30:55.614
Hey, Mr Stark, what should I do?

01:30:55.867 --> 01:30:56.698
What we discussed.

01:30:56.785 --> 01:30:57.845
Keep your distance, web them up.

01:30:57.869 --> 01:30:59.076
Okay, copy that.

01:31:03.959 --> 01:31:05.450
<i>Move, Captain.</i>

01:31:05.710 --> 01:31:07.292
<i>I won't ask a second time.</i>

01:31:09.631 --> 01:31:11.151
<i>Look, I really don't want to hurt you.</i>

01:31:11.758 --> 01:31:13.169
I wouldn't stress about it.

01:31:25.397 --> 01:31:26.729
What the hell is that?

01:31:26.898 --> 01:31:28.981
Everyone's got a gimmick now.

01:31:35.532 --> 01:31:36.898
You have a metal arm?

01:31:37.075 --> 01:31:38.611
That is awesome, dude.

01:31:40.370 --> 01:31:41.810
You have the right to remain silent!

01:31:56.594 --> 01:31:57.954
<i>Sorry, Cap, this won't kill you...</i>

01:31:58.054 --> 01:31:59.374
but it ain't gonna tickle either.

01:32:04.602 --> 01:32:06.514
<i>Wanda, I think you hurt
Vision's feelings.</i>

01:32:06.688 --> 01:32:08.099
You locked me in my room.

01:32:08.314 --> 01:32:09.754
<i>Okay, first, that's an exaggeration.</i>

01:32:09.816 --> 01:32:12.149
<i>Second, I did it to protect you.</i>

01:32:12.402 --> 01:32:13.609
<i>- Hey, Clint.</i>
- Hey, man.

01:32:13.820 --> 01:32:15.436
<i>Clearly, retirement doesn't suit you.</i>

01:32:15.697 --> 01:32:17.154
<i>You got tired of shooting golf?</i>

01:32:17.323 --> 01:32:19.690
Well, I played 18, shot 18.

01:32:20.618 --> 01:32:21.825
Just can't seem to miss.

01:32:24.456 --> 01:32:25.742
<i>First time for everything.</i>

01:32:25.915 --> 01:32:26.915
Made you look.

01:32:37.469 --> 01:32:39.176
<i>Multiple contusions detected.</i>

01:32:39.345 --> 01:32:40.961
Yeah, I detected that, too.

01:32:48.855 --> 01:32:49.891
Oh, God!

01:32:51.191 --> 01:32:52.807
Hey, buddy, I think you lost this!

01:32:58.364 --> 01:32:59.525
Ahh!

01:33:04.913 --> 01:33:06.199
Those wings carbon fibre?

01:33:06.414 --> 01:33:07.694
Is this stuff coming out of you?

01:33:07.957 --> 01:33:09.518
That would explain
the rigidity-flexibility ratio,

01:33:09.542 --> 01:33:11.062
which, gotta say, that's awesome, man.

01:33:11.127 --> 01:33:12.855
I don't know if you've
been in a fight before...

01:33:12.879 --> 01:33:14.559
but there's usually not this much talking.

01:33:14.631 --> 01:33:15.667
All right, sorry. My bad.

01:33:20.762 --> 01:33:22.378
Guys, look, I'd love to keep this up,

01:33:22.472 --> 01:33:24.088
but I've only got one job here today...

01:33:24.349 --> 01:33:27.308
and I gotta impress Mr Stark,
so, I'm really sorry.

01:33:30.939 --> 01:33:32.931
You couldn't have done that earlier?

01:33:33.399 --> 01:33:34.560
I hate you.

01:33:41.157 --> 01:33:42.157
<i>Great.</i>

01:33:42.367 --> 01:33:43.733
<i>Hey, Cap, heads-up!</i>

01:33:45.453 --> 01:33:46.819
<i>Throw it at this.</i>

01:33:47.413 --> 01:33:48.449
<i>Now!</i>

01:33:51.960 --> 01:33:53.246
<i>Oh, come on!</i>

01:33:56.214 --> 01:33:59.002
<i>Oh, man, I thought it was a water truck.</i>

01:33:59.717 --> 01:34:01.049
<i>Uh, sorry.</i>

01:34:03.054 --> 01:34:04.386
<i>All right, now I'm pissed.</i>

01:34:05.348 --> 01:34:06.680
Is this part of the plan?

01:34:06.850 --> 01:34:08.386
<i>Well, my plan was go easy on them.</i>

01:34:08.476 --> 01:34:09.557
<i>You wanna switch it up?</i>

01:34:12.021 --> 01:34:13.021
There's our ride.

01:34:15.483 --> 01:34:16.483
Come on!

01:34:25.451 --> 01:34:26.532
Captain Rogers...

01:34:27.579 --> 01:34:30.572
I know you believe
what you're doing is right.

01:34:31.374 --> 01:34:33.206
But for the collective good...

01:34:33.376 --> 01:34:35.709
you must surrender now.

01:34:52.812 --> 01:34:54.428
What do we do, Cap?

01:34:55.440 --> 01:34:56.897
We fight.

01:34:58.484 --> 01:35:00.100
This is gonna end well.

01:35:06.868 --> 01:35:08.279
They're not stopping.

01:35:08.453 --> 01:35:09.453
Neither are we.

01:35:40.443 --> 01:35:41.559
We're still friends, right?

01:35:41.736 --> 01:35:43.193
Depends on how hard you hit me.

01:35:52.080 --> 01:35:54.037
You were pulling your punches.

01:35:58.461 --> 01:35:59.668
I didn't kill your father.

01:35:59.921 --> 01:36:01.537
<i>Then why did you run?</i>

01:36:19.732 --> 01:36:21.772
That thing does not obey
the laws of physics at all.

01:36:22.026 --> 01:36:23.963
Look, kid, there's a lot going on here
that you don't understand.

01:36:23.987 --> 01:36:25.569
Mr Stark said you'd say that. Wow.

01:36:35.081 --> 01:36:37.118
He also said to go for your legs.

01:36:44.590 --> 01:36:45.590
Ahhh!

01:36:48.886 --> 01:36:50.218
Clint, can you get him off me?

01:36:50.388 --> 01:36:51.549
Buckled in?

01:36:51.723 --> 01:36:53.134
<i>Yeah. No, I'm good.</i>

01:36:53.308 --> 01:36:55.345
<i>I'm good, Arrow Guy. Let's go!</i>

01:37:17.081 --> 01:37:18.447
Stark tell you anything else?

01:37:18.624 --> 01:37:21.492
That you're wrong.
You think you're right.

01:37:21.919 --> 01:37:23.285
That makes you dangerous.

01:37:28.301 --> 01:37:29.712
Guess he had a point.

01:37:34.807 --> 01:37:36.924
You got heart, kid. Where you from?

01:37:37.602 --> 01:37:38.809
Queens.

01:37:40.438 --> 01:37:41.438
Brooklyn.

01:37:47.403 --> 01:37:48.439
<i>Friday?</i>

01:37:48.529 --> 01:37:49.798
<i>We have some
weapon systems offline.</i>

01:37:49.822 --> 01:37:50.822
What?

01:37:51.157 --> 01:37:53.399
<i>Oh, you're gonna have to
take this into the shop.</i>

01:37:53.701 --> 01:37:55.033
Who's speaking?

01:37:55.203 --> 01:37:58.913
<i>It's your conscience.
We don't talk a lot these days.</i>

01:37:59.123 --> 01:38:00.123
Friday?

01:38:00.208 --> 01:38:01.528
<i>Deploying fire
suppression system.</i>

01:38:02.668 --> 01:38:03.668
<i>Uh-oh.</i>

01:38:05.630 --> 01:38:06.630
<i>Oh, boy!</i>

01:38:09.342 --> 01:38:10.342
<i>Whoa!</i>

01:38:15.973 --> 01:38:18.056
We gotta go.
That guy's probably in Siberia by now.

01:38:18.351 --> 01:38:19.592
We gotta draw out the flyers.

01:38:19.769 --> 01:38:21.510
I'll take Vision, you get to the jet.

01:38:21.813 --> 01:38:23.429
No, you get to the jet!

01:38:23.564 --> 01:38:24.564
<i>Both of you!</i>

01:38:26.984 --> 01:38:28.462
The rest of us aren't getting out of here.

01:38:28.486 --> 01:38:29.630
As much as I hate to admit it...

01:38:29.654 --> 01:38:31.111
<i>if we're gonna win this one,</i>

01:38:31.197 --> 01:38:32.779
<i>some of us might have to lose it.</i>

01:38:32.949 --> 01:38:34.986
<i>This isn't the real fight, Steve.</i>

01:38:35.159 --> 01:38:36.695
All right, Sam. What's the play?

01:38:36.994 --> 01:38:39.077
We need a diversion. Something big.

01:38:40.832 --> 01:38:42.448
<i>I got something kinda big.</i>

01:38:42.542 --> 01:38:43.874
<i>But I can't hold it very long.</i>

01:38:44.293 --> 01:38:46.285
<i>On my signal, run like hell.</i>

01:38:46.504 --> 01:38:49.087
<i>And if I tear myself in half...
don't come back for me.</i>

01:38:49.173 --> 01:38:50.317
He's gonna tear himself in half?

01:38:50.341 --> 01:38:51.798
You sure about this, Scott?

01:38:52.009 --> 01:38:53.341
<i>I do it all the time.</i>

01:38:53.553 --> 01:38:55.340
<i>I mean, once. In a lab.</i>

01:38:55.513 --> 01:38:57.175
<i>Then I passed out.</i>

01:38:57.348 --> 01:38:59.180
<i>I'm the boss, I'm the boss, I'm the boss.</i>

01:39:15.241 --> 01:39:16.732
Holy shit!

01:39:21.038 --> 01:39:22.904
Okay, tiny dude is big now.
He's big now.

01:39:24.959 --> 01:39:26.040
I guess that's the signal.

01:39:26.294 --> 01:39:27.751
Way to go, Tic Tac!

01:39:29.630 --> 01:39:31.041
Give me back my Rhodey.

01:39:34.719 --> 01:39:35.926
I got him.

01:39:58.576 --> 01:40:01.114
Okay, anybody on our side
hiding any shocking

01:40:01.204 --> 01:40:03.056
and fantastic abilities
they'd like to disclose...

01:40:03.080 --> 01:40:04.196
I'm open to suggestions.

01:40:12.340 --> 01:40:13.956
<i>You wanna get to them...</i>

01:40:14.133 --> 01:40:15.249
<i>you gotta go through me.</i>

01:40:26.229 --> 01:40:27.345
<i>Uh-huh.</i>

01:40:42.286 --> 01:40:43.743
We haven't met yet.

01:40:46.332 --> 01:40:47.948
- I'm Clint.
<i>- I don't care.</i>

01:41:02.181 --> 01:41:03.217
Whoa!

01:41:08.271 --> 01:41:09.271
Ahhh!

01:41:15.861 --> 01:41:16.861
Get off!

01:41:31.752 --> 01:41:33.459
<i>Somethingjust flew in me!</i>

01:41:57.695 --> 01:41:58.695
You're not gonna stop.

01:41:59.363 --> 01:42:00.363
You know I can't.

01:42:01.324 --> 01:42:02.440
I'm gonna regret this.

01:42:06.120 --> 01:42:07.406
Go.

01:42:13.085 --> 01:42:15.122
Hey, guys, you ever see
that really old movie,

01:42:15.212 --> 01:42:17.124
<i>Empire Strikes Back?</i>

01:42:17.381 --> 01:42:18.713
<i>Jesus, Tony, how old is this guy?</i>

01:42:18.883 --> 01:42:20.027
I don't know, I didn't carbon-date him.

01:42:20.051 --> 01:42:21.051
He's on the young side.

01:42:23.095 --> 01:42:26.213
You know that part
where they're on the snow planet...

01:42:27.475 --> 01:42:28.966
with the walking thingies?

01:42:31.395 --> 01:42:32.581
Maybe the kid's onto something.

01:42:32.605 --> 01:42:33.605
High now, Tony. Go high.

01:42:42.073 --> 01:42:43.073
Yes!

01:42:43.616 --> 01:42:45.198
That was awesome!

01:42:59.924 --> 01:43:02.917
Does anyone have any orange slices?

01:43:08.474 --> 01:43:09.474
Kid, you all right?

01:43:09.684 --> 01:43:10.684
Whoa!

01:43:11.602 --> 01:43:14.686
Same side. Guess who. Hi. It's me.

01:43:14.855 --> 01:43:15.936
- Hey, man.
- Yeah.

01:43:16.107 --> 01:43:17.314
- That was scary.
- Yeah.

01:43:17.483 --> 01:43:19.099
You're done, all right?

01:43:19.276 --> 01:43:20.276
What? I'm good, I'm fine.

01:43:20.319 --> 01:43:21.421
You did a good job. Stay down.

01:43:21.445 --> 01:43:22.756
No, it's good. I gotta get him back.

01:43:22.780 --> 01:43:23.924
You're going home or I'll call Aunt May!

01:43:23.948 --> 01:43:25.109
- Dude.
- You're done!

01:43:25.282 --> 01:43:26.318
Wait.

01:43:26.492 --> 01:43:29.485
Mr Stark, wait.
I'm not done. I'm not...

01:43:31.664 --> 01:43:33.951
Okay, I'm done. I'm done.

01:43:50.141 --> 01:43:52.349
I said
I'd help you find him, not catch him.

01:43:52.893 --> 01:43:54.475
There's a difference.

01:44:01.318 --> 01:44:02.318
I'm sorry.

01:44:02.903 --> 01:44:03.984
Me, too.

01:44:04.905 --> 01:44:05.905
It's as I said.

01:44:06.407 --> 01:44:08.069
Catastrophe.

01:44:21.005 --> 01:44:22.837
Vision, I got a bandit on my six.

01:44:27.595 --> 01:44:28.595
<i>Vision! You copy?</i>

01:44:28.763 --> 01:44:30.755
<i>Target his thruster,
turn him into a glider.</i>

01:44:45.946 --> 01:44:47.062
<i>Rhodey!</i>

01:44:48.866 --> 01:44:50.653
Tony, I'm flying dead stick.

01:44:58.876 --> 01:45:00.242
Rhodes!

01:45:12.598 --> 01:45:14.055
Read vitals.

01:45:14.225 --> 01:45:15.466
<i>Heartbeat detected.</i>

01:45:15.643 --> 01:45:17.635
<i>Emergency medical is on its way.</i>

01:45:22.817 --> 01:45:23.817
I'm sorry.

01:45:45.714 --> 01:45:47.421
- this is room 201...

01:45:48.759 --> 01:45:50.375
Bacon and black coffee again today?

01:45:51.762 --> 01:45:53.298
You know me so well...

01:45:54.932 --> 01:45:56.764
Hello? Your breakfast is here.

01:45:57.768 --> 01:45:58.768
May I let myself in?

01:46:23.836 --> 01:46:25.452
What's gonna happen to your friends?

01:46:34.054 --> 01:46:35.590
Whatever it is...

01:46:36.181 --> 01:46:37.797
I'll deal with it.

01:46:40.895 --> 01:46:42.727
I don't know if I'm worth all this, Steve.

01:46:50.195 --> 01:46:51.811
What you did all those years...

01:46:52.865 --> 01:46:54.356
It wasn't you.

01:46:55.200 --> 01:46:56.987
You didn't have a choice.

01:46:58.162 --> 01:46:59.778
I know.

01:47:02.374 --> 01:47:04.582
But I did it.

01:47:18.807 --> 01:47:20.924
How did this happen?

01:47:21.143 --> 01:47:23.135
I became distracted.

01:47:25.439 --> 01:47:27.556
I didn't think that was possible.

01:47:28.984 --> 01:47:30.646
Neither did I.

01:47:47.211 --> 01:47:50.204
The doctors say
he shattered L4 through S1.

01:47:50.381 --> 01:47:53.124
Extreme laceration to the spinal cord.

01:47:53.300 --> 01:47:55.917
Probably looking at
some form of paralysis.

01:47:59.264 --> 01:48:00.800
Steve's not gonna stop.

01:48:01.600 --> 01:48:02.636
If you don't either,

01:48:02.726 --> 01:48:04.120
Rhodey's gonna be
the best case scenario.

01:48:04.144 --> 01:48:05.305
You let them go, Nat.

01:48:05.479 --> 01:48:06.515
We played this wrong.

01:48:06.689 --> 01:48:07.930
"We"?

01:48:08.399 --> 01:48:09.435
Boy, it must be hard to

01:48:09.525 --> 01:48:11.085
shake the whole
double agent thing, huh?

01:48:11.110 --> 01:48:12.817
It sticks in the DNA.

01:48:14.238 --> 01:48:16.821
Are you incapable
of letting go of your ego...

01:48:17.116 --> 01:48:19.073
for one goddamn second?

01:48:23.414 --> 01:48:25.622
T'Challa told Ross what you did, so...

01:48:26.959 --> 01:48:28.575
they're coming for you.

01:48:29.628 --> 01:48:32.371
I'm not the one that needs
to watch their back.

01:48:41.015 --> 01:48:42.381
What am I looking at, Friday?

01:48:42.474 --> 01:48:44.841
<i>Priority upload
from Berlin police.</i>

01:48:47.896 --> 01:48:49.387
Fire up the chopper.

01:48:55.362 --> 01:48:57.149
<i>The Task Force
called for a psychiatrist</i>

01:48:57.322 --> 01:48:58.938
<i>as soon as Barnes was captured.</i>

01:48:59.158 --> 01:49:01.445
<i>The UN dispatched
Doctor Theo Broussard</i>

01:49:01.577 --> 01:49:02.909
<i>from Geneva within the hour.</i>

01:49:03.078 --> 01:49:04.740
<i>He was met by this man.</i>

01:49:04.913 --> 01:49:05.974
Did you run
facial recognition yet?

01:49:05.998 --> 01:49:06.998
<i>What do I look like?</i>

01:49:07.416 --> 01:49:09.296
Uh, I don't know.
I've been picturing a redhead.

01:49:09.460 --> 01:49:10.996
<i>You must be thinking of someone else.</i>

01:49:11.128 --> 01:49:12.164
Must be.

01:49:12.337 --> 01:49:15.000
<i>The fake doctor is actually
Colonel Helmut Zemo.</i>

01:49:16.258 --> 01:49:18.420
<i>Sokovian Intelligence.</i>

01:49:19.511 --> 01:49:21.468
<i>Zemo ran Echo Scorpion...</i>

01:49:21.638 --> 01:49:24.096
<i>a Sokovian covert kill squad.</i>

01:49:26.310 --> 01:49:27.801
What happened to the real Broussard?

01:49:27.895 --> 01:49:29.761
<i>He was found dead
in a Berlin hotel room.</i>

01:49:29.938 --> 01:49:32.646
<i>Where police also found
a wig and facial prosthesis...</i>

01:49:32.816 --> 01:49:36.856
<i>approximating the appearance
of one James Buchanan Barnes.</i>

01:49:37.905 --> 01:49:39.692
Son of a bitch.

01:49:41.700 --> 01:49:43.657
- Get this to Ross.
<i>- Yes, boss.</i>

01:51:17.296 --> 01:51:19.162
<i>This is Raft Prison Control.</i>

01:51:19.298 --> 01:51:21.756
<i>You're cleared for landing, Mr Stark.</i>

01:51:54.208 --> 01:51:56.165
So? You got the files?

01:51:56.418 --> 01:51:57.579
Let's reroute the satellites,

01:51:57.753 --> 01:51:59.665
start facial scanning for this Zemo guy.

01:51:59.838 --> 01:52:01.921
You seriously think
I'm gonna listen to you

01:52:02.299 --> 01:52:04.131
after that fiasco in Leipzig?

01:52:04.343 --> 01:52:06.630
You're lucky you're not
in one of these cells.

01:52:37.459 --> 01:52:40.076
The Futurist, gentlemen!

01:52:40.254 --> 01:52:42.712
The Futurist is here!

01:52:42.881 --> 01:52:44.167
He sees all!

01:52:45.175 --> 01:52:48.259
He knows what's best for you,
whether you like it or not.

01:52:48.845 --> 01:52:49.845
Give me a break, Barton.

01:52:50.097 --> 01:52:52.555
<i>I had no idea
they'd put you here. Come on.</i>

01:52:53.183 --> 01:52:55.846
Yeah, well, you knew
they'd put us somewhere, Tony.

01:52:56.061 --> 01:52:59.179
Yeah, but not some
super-max floating ocean pokey.

01:52:59.356 --> 01:53:01.723
This place is for maniacs.
This is a place for...

01:53:01.900 --> 01:53:03.186
Criminals?

01:53:04.403 --> 01:53:06.190
Criminals, Tony.

01:53:06.697 --> 01:53:09.030
Think that's the word you're looking for.

01:53:10.325 --> 01:53:11.361
Right?

01:53:11.994 --> 01:53:14.031
That didn't used to mean me.

01:53:14.246 --> 01:53:15.657
Or Sam, or Wanda.

01:53:15.914 --> 01:53:17.450
But here we are.

01:53:17.624 --> 01:53:19.286
- Because you broke the law.
- Yeah.

01:53:19.459 --> 01:53:20.459
I didn't make you.

01:53:21.920 --> 01:53:23.960
- La, la, la, la, la...
- You read it, you broke it.

01:53:25.048 --> 01:53:27.210
You're all grown up,
you got a wife and kids.

01:53:27.342 --> 01:53:28.695
I don't understand, why didn't you

01:53:28.719 --> 01:53:30.639
think about them before
you chose the wrong side?

01:53:31.763 --> 01:53:33.720
You gotta watch your back with this guy.

01:53:35.017 --> 01:53:37.134
There's a chance he's gonna break it.

01:53:38.645 --> 01:53:41.854
Hank Pym always said
you never can trust a Stark.

01:53:42.691 --> 01:53:44.102
Who are you?

01:53:44.860 --> 01:53:46.522
Come on, man.

01:53:48.030 --> 01:53:49.066
How's Rhodes?

01:53:49.239 --> 01:53:52.073
They're flying him to
Columbia Medical tomorrow...

01:53:52.159 --> 01:53:53.320
so fingers crossed.

01:53:54.995 --> 01:53:56.452
What do you need? They feed you yet?

01:53:58.665 --> 01:54:00.156
You're the good cop, now?

01:54:00.876 --> 01:54:02.812
I'm just the guy who needs
to know where Steve went.

01:54:02.836 --> 01:54:04.418
Well, you better go get a bad cop...

01:54:04.588 --> 01:54:06.774
because you're gonna have to
go Mark Fuhrman on my ass...

01:54:06.798 --> 01:54:08.710
to get information out of me.

01:54:08.967 --> 01:54:10.833
Well, I just knocked
the A out of their AV.

01:54:11.053 --> 01:54:13.921
We got about 30 seconds before
they realise it's not their equipment.

01:54:14.890 --> 01:54:15.926
What'd you do?

01:54:16.099 --> 01:54:17.635
Get it back up!

01:54:18.727 --> 01:54:19.727
Just look.

01:54:20.729 --> 01:54:22.140
Because that...

01:54:22.314 --> 01:54:24.394
is the fellow who was
supposed to interrogate Barnes.

01:54:26.026 --> 01:54:28.564
Clearly, I made a mistake.
Sam, I was wrong.

01:54:28.862 --> 01:54:30.273
That's a first.

01:54:30.364 --> 01:54:31.980
Cap is definitely off the reservation...

01:54:32.074 --> 01:54:33.914
but he's about to need
all the help he can get.

01:54:34.117 --> 01:54:35.219
We don't know each other very well.

01:54:35.243 --> 01:54:36.324
You don't have to...

01:54:36.411 --> 01:54:38.619
Hey, it's all right.

01:54:46.546 --> 01:54:48.162
Look, I'll tell you...

01:54:48.340 --> 01:54:51.174
but you have to go alone and as a friend.

01:54:52.969 --> 01:54:54.005
Easy.

01:54:56.973 --> 01:54:57.973
Stark?

01:54:58.600 --> 01:55:00.262
Did he give you anything on Rogers?

01:55:00.435 --> 01:55:01.555
Nope. Told me to go to hell.

01:55:01.603 --> 01:55:03.435
I'm going back to the compound instead,

01:55:03.563 --> 01:55:05.520
but you can call me anytime.

01:55:05.690 --> 01:55:07.770
I'll put you on hold.
I like to watch the line blink.

01:56:16.887 --> 01:56:18.489
You remember that time
we had to ride back

01:56:18.513 --> 01:56:20.721
from Rockaway Beach
in the back of that freezer truck?

01:56:20.807 --> 01:56:23.049
Was that the time
we used our train money

01:56:23.143 --> 01:56:24.304
to buy hot dogs?

01:56:24.394 --> 01:56:27.478
You blew three bucks trying to win
that stuffed bear for a redhead.

01:56:28.190 --> 01:56:29.190
What was her name, again?

01:56:29.399 --> 01:56:31.106
Dolores. You called her Dot.

01:56:31.651 --> 01:56:33.411
She's gotta be
a hundred years old right now.

01:56:33.570 --> 01:56:34.606
So are we, pal.

01:56:44.456 --> 01:56:46.539
He can't have
been here more than a few hours.

01:56:46.708 --> 01:56:48.700
Long enough to wake them up.

01:57:30.877 --> 01:57:31.877
You ready?

01:57:32.045 --> 01:57:33.045
Yeah.

01:57:46.643 --> 01:57:48.635
You seem a little defensive.

01:57:49.980 --> 01:57:51.141
It's been a long day.

01:57:51.940 --> 01:57:53.772
At ease, Soldier.
I'm not currently after you.

01:57:53.942 --> 01:57:55.149
Then why are you here?

01:57:56.236 --> 01:57:58.899
Could be your story's not so crazy.

01:57:59.072 --> 01:58:00.072
Maybe.

01:58:01.700 --> 01:58:04.488
Ross has no idea I'm here.
I'd like to keep it that way.

01:58:05.579 --> 01:58:07.571
Otherwise, I gotta arrest myself.

01:58:08.873 --> 01:58:10.553
Well, that sounds like a lot of paperwork.

01:58:14.212 --> 01:58:15.498
It's good to see you, Tony.

01:58:15.714 --> 01:58:16.714
You too, Cap.

01:58:17.841 --> 01:58:20.083
Hey, Manchurian Candidate,
you're killing me.

01:58:20.176 --> 01:58:22.168
There's a truce here. You can drop...

01:58:42.115 --> 01:58:43.447
<i>I got heat signatures.</i>

01:58:43.617 --> 01:58:45.074
How many?

01:58:46.119 --> 01:58:47.985
<i>Uh, one.</i>

01:59:06.640 --> 01:59:08.882
<i>If it's any comfort,</i>

01:59:09.017 --> 01:59:10.508
<i>they died in their sleep.</i>

01:59:17.567 --> 01:59:20.651
<i>Did you really think
I wanted more of you?</i>

01:59:21.821 --> 01:59:23.528
What the hell?

01:59:24.324 --> 01:59:26.111
<i>I'm grateful to them, though.</i>

01:59:27.202 --> 01:59:28.738
<i>They brought you here.</i>

01:59:33.458 --> 01:59:35.165
<i>Please, Captain.</i>

01:59:35.335 --> 01:59:37.122
<i>The Soviets built
this chamber to withstand</i>

01:59:37.212 --> 01:59:39.795
<i>the launch blast of UR-100 rockets.</i>

01:59:39.964 --> 01:59:41.751
<i>I'm betting I could beat that.</i>

01:59:41.925 --> 01:59:43.632
<i>Oh, I'm sure you could, Mr Stark.</i>

01:59:44.177 --> 01:59:45.668
<i>Given time.</i>

01:59:46.179 --> 01:59:47.761
<i>But then you'd never know
why you came.</i>

01:59:47.972 --> 01:59:50.430
You killed innocent people in Vienna
just to bring us here?

01:59:57.232 --> 02:00:00.851
I've thought about
nothing else for over a year.

02:00:01.528 --> 02:00:03.269
I studied you.

02:00:03.780 --> 02:00:05.191
I followed you.

02:00:05.824 --> 02:00:07.611
But now that you're standing here...

02:00:07.784 --> 02:00:09.776
I just realised...

02:00:11.955 --> 02:00:14.447
there's a bit of green
in the blue of your eyes.

02:00:16.876 --> 02:00:19.334
How nice to find a flaw.

02:00:19.921 --> 02:00:21.503
You're Sokovian.

02:00:22.674 --> 02:00:24.165
Is that what this is about?

02:00:24.342 --> 02:00:27.835
Sokovia was a failed state
long before you blew it to hell.

02:00:27.971 --> 02:00:29.087
No.

02:00:30.432 --> 02:00:33.391
I'm here because I made a promise.

02:00:36.604 --> 02:00:37.811
You lost someone?

02:00:41.693 --> 02:00:43.730
I lost everyone.

02:00:45.572 --> 02:00:47.154
And so will you.

02:00:53.455 --> 02:00:57.074
An empire toppled
by its enemies can rise again.

02:00:58.168 --> 02:01:00.285
But one which crumbles from within?

02:01:01.921 --> 02:01:03.412
That's dead.

02:01:04.549 --> 02:01:05.549
Forever.

02:01:14.392 --> 02:01:16.008
I know that road.

02:01:18.396 --> 02:01:19.396
What is this?

02:01:42.670 --> 02:01:44.286
<i>Help my wife.</i>

02:01:45.423 --> 02:01:47.710
<i>Please. Help.</i>

02:01:53.306 --> 02:01:54.387
<i>Sergeant Barnes?</i>

02:01:56.142 --> 02:01:57.474
<i>Howard!</i>

02:02:05.068 --> 02:02:06.104
<i>Howard!</i>

02:02:43.523 --> 02:02:45.105
No, Tony.

02:02:54.284 --> 02:02:55.491
Did you know?

02:02:57.996 --> 02:02:59.237
I didn't know it was him.

02:02:59.414 --> 02:03:01.827
Don't bullshit me, Rogers.
Did you know?

02:03:05.712 --> 02:03:06.748
Yes.

02:04:03.853 --> 02:04:05.185
Get out of here!

02:04:16.658 --> 02:04:17.364
It wasn't him, Tony.

02:04:17.533 --> 02:04:18.636
HYDRA had control of his mind!

02:04:18.660 --> 02:04:19.660
Move!

02:04:19.702 --> 02:04:20.702
It wasn't him!

02:04:29.712 --> 02:04:31.044
<i>Left bootjet failing.</i>

02:04:31.923 --> 02:04:34.040
<i>Flight systems compromised.</i>

02:04:34.759 --> 02:04:35.759
Ah, crap.

02:04:49.524 --> 02:04:51.231
He's not gonna stop. Go.

02:05:14.257 --> 02:05:15.257
Come on, come on.

02:05:15.425 --> 02:05:16.961
<i>Targeting system's
knackered, boss.</i>

02:05:17.176 --> 02:05:18.176
I'm eyeballing it.

02:05:36.779 --> 02:05:38.395
Do you even remember them?

02:05:38.573 --> 02:05:40.280
I remember all of them.

02:06:03.139 --> 02:06:05.131
This isn't gonna change what happened.

02:06:05.308 --> 02:06:06.799
I don't care.

02:06:07.351 --> 02:06:08.717
He killed my mom.

02:07:10.206 --> 02:07:11.788
<i>You should have
seen his little face.</i>

02:07:11.874 --> 02:07:13.536
<i>Just try, okay?</i>

02:07:13.709 --> 02:07:15.541
<i>I'm going to bed.</i>

02:07:15.711 --> 02:07:17.373
<i>I love you.</i>

02:07:25.346 --> 02:07:27.759
I almost killed the wrong man.

02:07:28.891 --> 02:07:30.883
Hardly an innocent one.

02:07:31.060 --> 02:07:32.892
This is all you wanted?

02:07:33.729 --> 02:07:36.221
To see them rip each other apart.

02:07:40.194 --> 02:07:42.811
My father lived outside the city.

02:07:43.739 --> 02:07:46.072
I thought we would be safe there.

02:07:46.701 --> 02:07:48.567
My son was excited.

02:07:48.744 --> 02:07:51.578
He could see the Iron Man
from the car window.

02:07:52.582 --> 02:07:55.791
I told my wife, "Don't worry.

02:07:55.960 --> 02:07:59.920
"They're fighting in the city.
We're miles from harm."

02:08:02.258 --> 02:08:04.591
When the dust cleared...

02:08:05.428 --> 02:08:07.795
and the screaming stopped...

02:08:08.556 --> 02:08:12.470
it took me two days
until I found their bodies.

02:08:14.812 --> 02:08:16.394
My father...

02:08:17.231 --> 02:08:20.770
still holding my wife and son in his arms.

02:08:25.239 --> 02:08:27.231
And the Avengers?

02:08:28.242 --> 02:08:29.983
They went home.

02:08:31.954 --> 02:08:34.116
I knew I couldn't kill them.

02:08:34.290 --> 02:08:36.782
More powerful men than me have tried.

02:08:39.003 --> 02:08:41.245
<i>But, if I could get them
to kill each other...</i>

02:08:45.801 --> 02:08:48.589
I'm sorry about your father.

02:08:49.013 --> 02:08:50.845
He seemed a good man.

02:08:52.642 --> 02:08:54.133
With a dutiful son.

02:08:58.856 --> 02:09:00.643
Vengeance has consumed you.

02:09:03.444 --> 02:09:05.777
It's consuming them.

02:09:09.700 --> 02:09:11.783
I am done letting it consume me.

02:09:15.498 --> 02:09:17.831
Justice will come soon enough.

02:09:21.170 --> 02:09:23.002
Tell that to the dead.

02:09:27.510 --> 02:09:30.218
The living are not done with you, yet.

02:09:33.057 --> 02:09:35.515
<i>You can't beat him
hand-to-hand.</i>

02:09:36.644 --> 02:09:37.805
Analyse his fight pattern.

02:09:38.104 --> 02:09:39.265
<i>Scanning.</i>

02:09:43.985 --> 02:09:45.021
<i>Countermeasures ready.</i>

02:09:47.196 --> 02:09:48.196
Let's kick his ass.

02:10:01.877 --> 02:10:03.163
He's my friend.

02:10:03.921 --> 02:10:04.957
So was I.

02:10:12.013 --> 02:10:14.096
<i>Stay down. Final warning.</i>

02:10:28.571 --> 02:10:30.733
I could do this all day.

02:11:37.098 --> 02:11:39.340
That shield doesn't belong to you.

02:11:40.976 --> 02:11:42.638
You don't deserve it.

02:11:42.812 --> 02:11:44.849
My father made that shield!

02:12:20.516 --> 02:12:22.348
Meals at 8 and 5.

02:12:22.518 --> 02:12:24.134
Toilet privileges twice a day.

02:12:26.522 --> 02:12:28.684
Raise your voice, zap.

02:12:29.358 --> 02:12:31.350
Touch the glass, zap.

02:12:31.694 --> 02:12:33.686
You step out of line, you deal with me.

02:12:33.863 --> 02:12:36.025
Please, step out of line, hmm?

02:12:38.242 --> 02:12:39.653
So how does it feel?

02:12:40.578 --> 02:12:43.036
To spend all that time, all that effort...

02:12:45.916 --> 02:12:50.035
to see it fail so spectacularly?

02:12:54.049 --> 02:12:55.290
Did it?

02:13:20.784 --> 02:13:21.900
It's just the first pass.

02:13:22.036 --> 02:13:23.036
Yeah.

02:13:23.078 --> 02:13:25.115
Give me some feedback,
anything you think of.

02:13:25.289 --> 02:13:27.952
Shock absorption, lateral movement.

02:13:28.584 --> 02:13:29.584
Cup holder?

02:13:29.752 --> 02:13:31.472
You may wanna think about
some AC down in...

02:13:31.587 --> 02:13:32.623
Ow.

02:13:35.216 --> 02:13:36.456
Let's go. I'll give you a hand.

02:13:36.592 --> 02:13:38.254
No. Don't help me.

02:13:41.472 --> 02:13:42.472
Ah.

02:13:54.318 --> 02:13:55.604
138.

02:13:56.445 --> 02:13:59.062
138 combat missions.

02:13:59.240 --> 02:14:00.981
That's how many I've flown, Tony.

02:14:01.242 --> 02:14:04.280
Every one of them
could've been my last, but I flew them.

02:14:06.163 --> 02:14:07.699
Because the fight needed to be fought.

02:14:08.207 --> 02:14:09.823
It's the same with these Accords.

02:14:10.501 --> 02:14:13.994
I signed because it was
the right thing to do.

02:14:15.965 --> 02:14:18.002
And yeah, this sucks. This is, uh...

02:14:19.301 --> 02:14:21.133
This is a bad beat.

02:14:23.180 --> 02:14:24.796
But it hasn't changed my mind.

02:14:26.475 --> 02:14:27.841
I don't think.

02:14:38.279 --> 02:14:39.645
- You okay?
- Oh, yeah.

02:14:42.992 --> 02:14:45.985
Are you Tony Stank?

02:14:46.203 --> 02:14:50.447
Yes, this is Tony Stank.
You're in the right place.

02:14:50.624 --> 02:14:52.331
Thank you for that!

02:14:52.501 --> 02:14:54.333
Never dropping that, by the way.

02:14:54.503 --> 02:14:56.415
"Table for one, Mr Stank.

02:14:56.505 --> 02:14:57.666
"Please, by the bathroom."

02:15:04.221 --> 02:15:05.221
<i>Tony...</i>

02:15:06.390 --> 02:15:08.347
<i>I'm glad you're back at the compound.</i>

02:15:08.517 --> 02:15:11.555
<i>I don't like the idea of you
rattling around a mansion by yourself.</i>

02:15:11.729 --> 02:15:13.095
<i>We all need family.</i>

02:15:14.523 --> 02:15:18.358
<i>The Avengers are yours.
Maybe more so than mine.</i>

02:15:19.153 --> 02:15:21.691
<i>I've been on my own since I was 18.</i>

02:15:22.489 --> 02:15:25.152
<i>I never really fit in anywhere,</i>

02:15:25.242 --> 02:15:27.074
<i>even in the Army.</i>

02:15:28.704 --> 02:15:31.868
<i>My faith's in people, I guess.</i>

02:15:32.041 --> 02:15:33.248
<i>Individuals.</i>

02:15:34.209 --> 02:15:37.247
<i>And I'm happy to say that,
for the most part...</i>

02:15:37.421 --> 02:15:39.037
<i>they haven't let me down.</i>

02:15:41.050 --> 02:15:43.542
<i>Which is why I can't
let them down either.</i>

02:15:47.514 --> 02:15:50.882
<i>Locks can be replaced,
but maybe they shouldn't.</i>

02:15:52.770 --> 02:15:54.887
<i>I know I hurt you, Tony.</i>

02:15:55.064 --> 02:15:58.148
<i>I guess I thought by not telling you
about your parents...</i>

02:15:58.233 --> 02:16:00.566
<i>I was sparing you...</i>

02:16:00.736 --> 02:16:03.399
<i>but I can see now that
I was really sparing myself.</i>

02:16:03.906 --> 02:16:05.898
<i>And I'm sorry.</i>

02:16:06.075 --> 02:16:08.237
<i>Hopefully one day you can understand.</i>

02:16:09.119 --> 02:16:10.860
<i>I wish we agreed on the Accords.</i>

02:16:10.954 --> 02:16:12.536
<i>I really do.</i>

02:16:12.706 --> 02:16:14.267
<i>I know you're doing what you believe in,</i>

02:16:14.291 --> 02:16:15.827
<i>and that's all any of us can do.</i>

02:16:15.918 --> 02:16:17.284
<i>That's all any of us should.</i>

02:16:17.378 --> 02:16:19.370
<i>Priority call
from Secretary Ross.</i>

02:16:19.463 --> 02:16:21.750
<i>There's been a breach
at the Raft prison.</i>

02:16:23.050 --> 02:16:24.791
Yeah, put him through.

02:16:25.928 --> 02:16:27.385
<i>Tony, we have a problem.</i>

02:16:27.471 --> 02:16:29.463
- Uh, please hold.
<i>- No, don't.</i>

02:16:32.226 --> 02:16:33.592
<i>So no matter what...</i>

02:16:34.770 --> 02:16:36.102
<i>I promise you...</i>

02:16:36.230 --> 02:16:37.892
<i>if you need us...</i>

02:16:38.774 --> 02:16:40.731
<i>if you need me...</i>

02:16:44.988 --> 02:16:46.274
<i>I'll be there.</i>

02:18:45.609 --> 02:18:46.645
You sure about this?

02:18:48.862 --> 02:18:50.728
I can't trust my own mind.

02:18:53.534 --> 02:18:56.117
So, until they figure out
how to get this stuff out of my head...

02:18:56.286 --> 02:18:58.744
I think going back under
is the best thing.

02:18:59.456 --> 02:19:00.947
For everybody.

02:19:23.230 --> 02:19:24.596
Thank you for this.

02:19:27.109 --> 02:19:29.146
Your friend and my father...

02:19:30.112 --> 02:19:31.944
they were both victims.

02:19:33.448 --> 02:19:36.782
If I can help one of them find peace...

02:19:39.621 --> 02:19:42.329
You know, if they find out he's here...

02:19:42.499 --> 02:19:44.536
they'll come for him.

02:19:46.461 --> 02:19:48.123
Let them try.

02:23:39.027 --> 02:23:43.442
<i>Hey, shady baby
I'm hot like the prodigal son</i>

02:23:48.411 --> 02:23:50.118
<i>Pick a petal
Eenie, meenie, miney, moe</i>

02:23:50.205 --> 02:23:53.073
<i>And flower You're the chosen one</i>

02:23:57.003 --> 02:24:01.623
<i>Well, your left hand's free
And your right's in a grip</i>

02:24:01.716 --> 02:24:06.256
<i>With another left hand
Watch his right hand slip</i>

02:24:06.346 --> 02:24:09.054
<i>Towards his gun</i>

02:24:09.141 --> 02:24:11.884
<i>Oh, no</i>

02:24:21.319 --> 02:24:25.563
<i>I tackle, we tussle
Oh, my days, we're rolling</i>

02:24:30.787 --> 02:24:35.782
<i>My right hand's gripped on his
Colt Single Action Army</i>

02:24:37.419 --> 02:24:39.331
<i>Oh, no</i>

02:24:39.421 --> 02:24:44.007
<i>Well, your left hand's free
And your right's in a grip</i>

02:24:44.092 --> 02:24:48.632
<i>With another left hand
Watch his right hand slip</i>

02:24:48.722 --> 02:24:51.339
<i>Towards his gun</i>

02:24:51.433 --> 02:24:54.221
<i>Oh, no</i>

02:24:54.311 --> 02:24:56.598
<i>N-E-O, O-M-G
Gee whiz</i>

02:24:56.688 --> 02:24:58.930
<i>Girl, you're the one for me</i>

02:25:03.778 --> 02:25:05.610
<i>Though your man's bigger than I am</i>

02:25:05.697 --> 02:25:10.362
<i>Oh, my days He disagrees</i>

02:25:10.452 --> 02:25:12.444
<i>Oh, no</i>

02:25:12.537 --> 02:25:13.948
<i>Speak easy</i>

02:25:31.014 --> 02:25:33.381
<i>Well, my left hand's free</i>

02:25:33.475 --> 02:25:35.717
<i>Oh</i>

02:25:35.810 --> 02:25:38.052
<i>Well, my left hand's free</i>

02:25:38.146 --> 02:25:40.433
<i>Oh</i>

02:25:40.523 --> 02:25:42.435
<i>Well, my left hand's free</i>

02:25:42.525 --> 02:25:43.561
<i>Oh</i>

02:25:43.652 --> 02:25:45.814
<i>Oh, no</i>

02:25:45.904 --> 02:25:50.524
<i>Hey, shady baby
I'm hot like the prodigal son</i>

02:25:55.538 --> 02:25:57.074
<i>Pick a petal
Eenie, meenie, miney, moe</i>

02:25:57.165 --> 02:26:00.033
<i>And flower You're the chosen one</i>

02:26:04.047 --> 02:26:06.289
<i>Well, your left hand's free</i>

02:26:06.383 --> 02:26:08.670
<i>Oh</i>

